  <note>
    <title>Adrenal gland_cortical adenoma</title>
    <created>20150807T013245Z</created>
    <updated>20240108T032138Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br clear="none" />DIAGNOSIS:<br clear="none" /><span>Adrenal</span> cortical adenoma, _ <span>adrenal</span> gland<br clear="none" />_retroperitoneal laparoscopic adrenalectomy <br clear="none" /><br clear="none" />REFERENCE:<br clear="none" /></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:<br clear="none" />Received is a tissue bloc measuring _ x _ x _ cm including <span>adrenal</span> gland tissue measuring _ x _x _ cm and _ gm. <br clear="none" />A tumor is seen measuring _ x _ x _ cm. It had been sectioned partially when received, and revealing golden-yellow appearance.<br clear="none" /><br clear="none" />Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:<br clear="none" /></div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div>MICROSCOPIC FINDING:<br clear="none" />Sections show a well-circumscribed tumor composed of lipid-laden clear cells and compact cells with eosinophilic cytoplasm, arranged in nests or cords with abundant vasculature. There is no cellular atypia. Mitosis is hardly identified. Focal lymphocytic infiltrate along the fibrous septa is noted.<br clear="none" /><br clear="none" /></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Adrenal gland_Weiss Criteris</title>
    <created>20161115T052902Z</created>
    <updated>20161117T012135Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>Histopathologic criteria proposed by Weiss
</div><div>-- High nuclear grade, Fuhrman criteria: absent (grade 2)
</div><div>-- >5 mitoses per 50 high -power fields: absent (&lt;1 mitosis per 50 high-power fields)
</div><div>-- Atypical mitotic figures: absent
</div><div>-- &lt;25% of tumor cells are clear cells: absent
</div><div>-- Diffuse architecture (>33% of tumor): present
</div><div>-- Necrosis: absent 
</div><div>-- Venous invasion (smooth muscle in wall): absent
</div><div>-- Sinusoidal invasion (no smooth muscle in wall): absent
</div><div>-- Capsular invasion: absent
</div><div><br/></div><div>The overall features are insufficient to diagnosed as malignancy based on criteria 
</div><div>proposed by Weiss. 
</div><div><br/></div><div><hr/></div><div><br/></div><div>

<div style="font-family:gotham, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">Modified Weiss (Weiss Revisited) System</span></div><div style="font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans;font-size:16px;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">Mitotic rate >5/50HPF</span></div><div style="font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans;font-size:16px;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">Atypical mitotic figures</span></div><div style="font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans;font-size:16px;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">Clear cells comprising&lt;25% of the tumor</span></div><div style="font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans;font-size:16px;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">Necrosis</span></div><div style="font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans;font-size:16px;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">Capsular invasion</span></div></div><div style="font-family:gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:14px;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;"><em>*Five criteria, each 0 or 1 (2"mitotic rate+2"cytoplasm +abnormal mitoses+necrosis+capsular invasion) for total of 7 possible points with 3 points diagnostic of malignancy</em></span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>AK</title>
    <created>20150724T021709Z</created>
    <updated>20210503T055847Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-family: Gulim; font-size: 12pt;">DIAGNOSIS:</span></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-family: Gulim; font-size: 12pt;">1.  </span><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Gulim;">Gangrene</span> <span style="font-family: Gulim; font-size: 12pt;"> , _ lower extremity, above-knee amputation</span></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-family: Gulim; font-size: 12pt;">2. Arteriosclerosis with _% obstruction, _ popliteal artery</span></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><div><font style="font-size: 12pt;"><br clear="none" /></font></div></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><div><font style="font-size: 12pt;"><br clear="none" /></font></div></div><div><font style="font-size: 12pt;"><br clear="none" /></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 12pt;"><br clear="none" /></font></div><div><span style="font-family: Gulim; font-size: 12pt;">GROSS DESCRIPTION:</span></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-family: Gulim; font-size: 12pt;">The specimen is composed of an amputated _right/left lower extremity (, with previous traumatic below-knee amputation stump), in fresh state. The thigh measures _ cm in length and _ cm</span></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-family: Gulim; font-size: 12pt;">in diameter. The lower leg measures _ from the knee to heel with a calf diameter of _ cm. The foot measures _ x _ cm.</span></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><div><font style="font-size: 12pt;"><br clear="none" /></font></div></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-family: Gulim; font-size: 12pt;">A. The skin over the lateral leg and plantar foot near 5th toe shows desquamation.</span></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-family: Gulim; font-size: 12pt;">B. The 2nd, 3rd, 4th and 5th toes exhibit blackish, gangrenous change.</span></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-family: Gulim; font-size: 12pt;">C. An ulceration measuring _x _ cm located on the 5th toe and metatarsal jointis also</span></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-family: Gulim; font-size: 12pt;">noted.</span></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-family: Gulim; font-size: 12pt;">* Necrosis is noted from the stump to posterior knee, measuring _ x _ cm.</span></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><div><font style="font-size: 12pt;"><br clear="none" /></font></div></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-family: Gulim; font-size: 12pt;">The popliteal artery demonstrates _moderate/severe arteriosclerosis.</span></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><div><font style="font-size: 12pt;"><br clear="none" /></font></div></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-family: Gulim; font-size: 12pt;">Representative sections are submitted and labeled as follow.</span></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-family: Gulim; font-size: 12pt;">RA-RB: gangrenous tissue</span></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-family: Gulim; font-size: 12pt;">RC: popliteal artery</span></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><div><font style="font-size: 12pt;"><br clear="none" /></font></div></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><div><font style="font-size: 12pt;"><br clear="none" /></font></div></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><div><font style="font-size: 12pt;"><br clear="none" /></font></div></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><div><font style="font-size: 12pt;"><br clear="none" /></font></div></div><div><font style="font-size: 12pt;"><br/></font></div><div><span style="font-family: Gulim; font-size: 12pt;">MICROSCOPIC DESCRIPTION:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: Gulim; font-size: 12pt;">The representative sections of the skin and soft tissues show liquefactive necrosis</span></div><div><span style="font-family: Gulim; font-size: 12pt;">with heavy PMN infiltration as well as lymphoplasmacytic cells infiltration in the</span></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-family: Gulim; font-size: 12pt;">adjacent viable tissue. The popliteal artery shows atheromatous plaques with 90%</span></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-family: Gulim; font-size: 12pt;">luminal obstruction.</span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
