    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>1. Gangrene, left right foot;</div><div>2. Arteriosclerosis with 80% obstruction, left right anterior  tibial artery</div><div>3. Arteriosclerosis with 60% obstruction, left  right posterior tibial artery</div><div>Below-knee amputation</div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div>The specimen is composed of an amputated lower leg and foot, in fresh state. It measures _____ cm from the proximal surgical end to heel with a calf diameter of _____ cm. The foot measures _ x _ cm.</div><div><br/></div><div>The toe had been amputated previously. The stump is necrotic, measuring x cm in dimensions.</div><div> </div><div>The skin over _ is blackish and gangrenous.</div><div><br/></div><div>An ulceration and necrosis measuring _ x _ cm located on the is (also) noted.</div><div><br/></div><div>The anterior and posterior tibial arteries both demonstrate</div><div>mild / moderate / severe arteriosclerosis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Representative sections are submitted and labeled as follow.</div><div>RA: gangrenous tissue</div><div>RB: anterior tibial artery</div><div>RC: posterior tibial artery</div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC DESCRIPTION:</div><div>Sections of the skin and soft tissue show liquefactive necrosis with heavy PMN infiltrate as well as lymphoplasmacytic cells infiltrate. Both the anterior and posterior tibial arteries show atheromatous plaques with calcification and luminal narrowing of __% and __%, respectively.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>BK 2</title>
