    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Necrotizing suppurative inflammation, right / left foot, below-knee amputation</div><div>Arteriosclerosis with ?% obstruction, right / left anterior tibial artery<br clear="none" />
Arteriosclerosis with ?% obstruction, right / left posterior tibial artery</div><p><br clear="none" /></p><div><br clear="none" />
GROSS DESCRIPTION:<br clear="none" />
The specimen is composed of an amputated lower leg and foot, in fresh state. It measures _____ cm from the proximal surgical end to heel with a calf diameter of _____ cm. The foot measures _ x _ cm.
<p><br clear="none" /></p></div><div>The toe had been amputated previously. The stump is necrotic, measuring x cm in dimensions.<br clear="none" /><br clear="none" />
The skin over _ is blackish and gangrenous.
<p><br clear="none" /></p></div><div>An ulceration and necrosis measuring _ x _ cm located on the is (also) noted.
<p><br clear="none" /></p></div><div>The anterior and posterior tibial arteries both demonstrate<br clear="none" />
mild / moderate / severe arteriosclerosis.
<p><br clear="none" /></p></div><div>Representative sections are submitted and labeled as follow.<br clear="none" />
RA: gangrenous tissue<br clear="none" />
RB: anterior tibial artery<br clear="none" />
RC: posterior tibial artery
<p><br clear="none" /></p></div><div>MICROSCOPIC DESCRIPTION:</div><div>The representative sections show necrotic skin with granulation tissue reaction,</div><div>accompanied by suppurative inflammation in the underlying dermis and subcutaneous</div><div>tissue. Both the anterior and posterior tibial arteries show atheromatous plaques with calcification and luminal narrowing of __% and __%, respectively.</div><div>The GMS and PAS stains are negative for fungal organism.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
