    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Ductal carcinoma in situ (T ), _ breast, OP____</div><div><br/></div><div>REFERENCE:</div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div>1. Breast (_ x _ x _ cm and _ gm) with overlying skin _and nipple_(_ x _ cm) and axillary fat (_ x _ x _ cm).</div><div>2. Tumor size: _ x _ x _ cm.</div><div>3. Tumor location: _ o'clock direction, _ cm to the nipple. (according to clinical information)</div><div>4. Margin distance:</div><div>- Base margin: _ cm</div><div>- Nearest lateral margin: _ cm</div><div>5. Other quadrants: unremarkable.</div><div>6. Two bottles of adipose tissue labeled as axillary lymph nodes measure(s) _ x _ x _ cm.</div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><br clear="none" /></div><div>Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:</div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><br clear="none" /></div><div>MICROSCOPIC FINDING:</div><div>1. Histological type: Ductal carcinoma in situ</div><div>2. Tumor size: mm</div><div>3. Nuclear Grade: 1/2/3</div><div>4. Architectural pattern:  <span style="line-height: 1.45;">Comedo/ Non-comedo (cribriform/papillary/miropapillary/solid)</span></div><div>5. Tumor necrosis:</div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">not identified</span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">present, focal (small foci or single cell necrosis) </span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">present, central (expansive “comedo” necrosis)</span></div><div>6. Microcalcification: absent/present (inside/outside the DCIS)</div><div>7. Peritumor lymphatic/vascular invasion: not identified</div><div>8. Margins: negative, closest margin ( mm)/Positive</div><div>9. Skin:</div><div>10. Nipple:</div><div>11. Axillary lymph node status: , compiled from the report of sentinel lymph node biopsy (201_-_-_)</div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><br clear="none" /></div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div>IMMUNOHISTOCHEMICAL STUDY: (Staining on section )</div><div>1. ER (Novocastra Laboratories, clone 6F11): _positive (_%)_Negative</div><div>2. PR (Novocastra Laboratories, clone 16): _positive (_%)_Negative</div><div>3. HER-2/Neu (DAKO, A0485): Positive (3+) /Equivocal (2+) /Negative (1+/0)</div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><br clear="none" /></div><div>Negative (0) : No staining, or membrane staining &lt;10% tumor</div><div>Negative (1+) : Incomplete membrane staining >=10% tumor</div><div>Equivocal (2+) : Weak-moderate complete membrane staining >=10%</div><div>Positive (3+) : Strong complete membrane staining >=10% tumor</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
