with overlying skin _and nipple measuring _ x _ cm. There is a _ cm well healed surgical scar on the skin. </div><div>Orientation: Present _Not present </div><div>12 o'clock direction: One long and one short
stitches</div><div>3 o'clock direction: Two short stitches</div><div>6 o'clock direction: No stitch</div><div>9 o'clock direction: Two long stitches.</div><div>A previous operative cavity is identified, measuring _ x _ x _ cm.</div><div>Location: _ o'clock direction, _ cm from the nipple (according to clinical information).</div><div>Margin distance from the cavity:
- Base margin: _ cm
- Nearest lateral margin: _ cm</div><div>Other quadrants: Grossly unremarkable.</div><div>Other specimen: </div><div><br/></div><div>Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:</div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC FINDING:</div><div style="padding-left:40px;">Sections of the operative cavity reveal multiple foci of residual ductal carcinoma in situ. Fat necrosis and foreign-body giant cell reaction are seen in the adjacent tissue, compatible with previous operation. Following descriptions are based on previous and present pathological findings.</div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC DESCRIPTION: </div><div><span style="color:red;">Histologic type: </span></div><div>Ductal carcinoma in situ</div><div>Paget disease</div><div>Encapsulated papillary
carcinoma without invasive carcinoma</div><div>Solid papillary carcinoma
without invasive carcinoma</div><div><span style="color:red;">Tumor size (mm): </span>_
mm, measured on the histologic slide;<span style="color:red;"> </span></div><div><span style="color:red;">Nuclear grade: _</span>Grade I (low) Grade II
(intermediate) Grade III (high) </div><div><span style="color:red;">Architectural pattern: _</span>Cribriform micropapillary
papillary solid </div><div><span style="color:red;">Necrosis: _</span>Not
identified</div><div>Present,
focal (small foci or single cell necrosis)</div><div>Present,
central (expansive comedo necrosis)<span style="color:red;"> </span></div><div><span style="color:red;">Extent of tumor: </span></div><div><span style="color:red;">Skin
involvement: _Free Not assessed. </span></div><div><span style="color:red;">Chest wall
invasion deeper than pectoralis muscle: Not assessed.</span></div><div>Nipple: <span style="color:red;">Not assessed.</span></div><div>Peritumoral lymphovascular invasion:
Absent</div><div>Perineural invasion: Absent </div><div>Microcalcification: _Absent / Present (inside
the DCIS and non-tumor mammary acini)</div><div><span style="color:red;">Surgical margin: _ mm
in distance.</span></div><div><span style="color:red;">Lymph nodes
(Positive/Total): Not assessed</span></div><div>Sentinel:
_/_<span style="color:red;">, compiled from the report of sentinel lymph node biopsy FS_.</span></div><div>Axillary:
_/_;</div><div> 
Extranodal extension: _Present _Absent  </div><div>Metastatic
size: _&lt;0.2
mm 0.2mm&lt; &lt;2 mm >2 mm </div><div><span style="color:red;">Treatment Effect:</span> Not applicable</div><div>Immunohistochemical study: (Performed
on section _) <span style="color:red;">(Results in previous
specimen _)</span></div><div>SMMHC highlights the
