  <note>
    <title>Breast_IDC</title>
    <created>20150723T234820Z</created>
    <updated>20260430T013205Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS: </div><div>Invasive ductal carcinoma () with axillary lymph node metastasis (), _ breast</div><div><br/></div><div>modified radical mastectomy</div><div> partial mastectomy</div><div> total mastectomy</div><div><br/></div><div>with sentinel lymph node biopsy</div><div> axillary lymph node dissection </div><div><br/></div><div>REFERENCE: </div><div><br/></div><div>NOTE: The pathologic findings of the sentinel lymph node status in the previous frozen section (201_-_-_) has been compiled into this report. </div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS FINDING:</div><div> The specimen received is a formalin-fixed breast tissue with overlying skin, including</div><div> nipple and attached axillary content.</div><div> 1. Breast (_ x _ x _ cm and _ gm) with overlying skin _and nipple_(_ x _ cm) and axillary fat (_ x _ x _ cm).</div><div> It had been sectioned partially when received.</div><div> 2. Tumor size: _ x _ x _ cm.</div><div> 3. Tumor location:  _ o'clock position of the breast, _ cm from the nipple * (according to clinical information)</div><div> 4. Margin distance: _ cm from the base; _ cm from the lateral margin.</div><div> 5. Other quadrants: unremarkable.</div><div> 6. Two bottles of adipose tissue labeled as axillary lymph nodes measure(s) _ x _ x _ cm. </div><div><br/></div><div>Representative sections are labeled as:</div><div><br/></div><div>R_: tumor</div><div> R_: base margin</div><div> R_: nearest lateral margin</div><div> R_: nipple and skin</div><div> R_: axillary LNs</div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC FINDINGS:</div><div>1. Histological type: invasive ductal carcinoma _invasive lobular carcinoma</div><div>2. Size of invasive carcinoma : mm (T )</div><div> 3. Histologic grade (Nottingham histologic score):</div><div> Grade I (score 3-5) / Grade II (score 6,7) / Grade III (score 8,9)</div><div> - Tubule formation: score 1/ 2/ 3</div><div>- Nuclear pleomorphism: score 1/ 2/ 3</div><div>- Mitotic count: score 1/ 2/ 3</div><div><br/></div><div>Majority of tumor greater than 75% (score = 1)</div><div>Moderate 10% to 75% (score = 2)</div><div> Minimal less than 10% (score = 3)</div><div> </div><div>Small regular nuclei (score = 1)</div><div> Moderate increase in size, etc (score = 2)</div><div> Marked variation in size, nucleoli, chromatin clumping, etc (score = 3)</div><div> </div><div>0- 3 mitoses per mm2 (score = 1)</div><div> 4-7 mitoses per mm2 (score = 2)</div><div> >= 8 mitoses per mm2 (score = 3)</div><div><br/></div><div>4. Extensive intraductal component: absent/ present, comedo/non-comedo type</div><div>Ductal carcinoma in situ component: _, comedo type_cribriform pattern</div><div> *present within the tumor though not >25% of the whole tumorous area</div><div> 5. Peritumor lymphatic/vascular invasion: present/not identified</div><div> 6. Nipple: free/Paget's disease</div><div> *There is tumor spreading along the underlying lactiferous duct. No intraepidermal involvement is seen.</div><div> 7. Skin involvement: Absent / Present (without ulceration / with ulceration / satellite skin foci)</div><div> 8. Chest wall invasion deeper than pectoralis muscle: not applicable /Absent / Present</div><div> 9. Margins:</div><div> - Base margin: negative, closest margin ( mm)/Positive</div><div> - Lateral margin: negative, closest margin ( mm)/Positive</div><div> 10. Axillary lymph node status: (_/_, pN_) with/without extranodal extension</div><div> *, compiled from the report of sentinel lymph node biopsy (FS_)</div><div> No. examined: _______</div><div> No. macrometastases (>2 mm): _____</div><div> No. micrometastases (>0.2 ~ 2 mm and/or >200 cells): _____</div><div> No. isolated tumor cells (&lt;=0.2 mm and &lt;=200 cells): _____</div><div> The axillary fat has been serially re-dissected again. Only _ lymph nodes are identified.</div><div> 11. Other significant lesion:</div><div> 12. Treatment Effect: _not applicable</div><div> Response to presurgical (neoadjuvant) therapy (if patient received) (T and N categories determined after treatment are indicated by the prefix “yp.”)</div><div> In the Breast</div><div> ___ No definite response to presurgical therapy in the invasive carcinoma</div><div> ___ Probable or definite response to presurgical therapy in the invasive carcinoma</div><div> ___ No residual invasive carcinoma is present in the breast after presurgical therapy </div><div><br/></div><div>IMMUNOHISTOCHEMICAL STUDY: (Staining on section )</div><div>IMMUNOHISTOCHEMICAL STUDY: (Results reported in previous specimen _)</div><div> 1. ER (Novocastra Laboratories, clone 6F11): positive /Negative ( %).</div><div> 2. PR (Novocastra Laboratories, clone 16): positive /Negative ( %).</div><div> 3. HER-2/Neu (DAKO, A0485): Positive (3+) /Equivocal (2+) /Negative (1+/0)</div><div> 4. Ki-67 index: (cut point: &lt;14% or >=14%) </div><div><br/></div><div>Negative (0) : No staining, or membrane staining &lt;10% tumor</div><div> Negative (1+) : Incomplete membrane staining >=10% tumor</div><div> Equivocal (2+) : Weak-moderate complete membrane staining >=10%</div><div> Positive (3+) : Strong complete membrane staining >=10% tumor</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
