      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>1. Adenocarcinoma ( T ) with/ without regional lymph nodes metastasis ( , N ), _</div><div>2. Free of tumor, bilateral surgical margins and appendix</div><div>Right hemicolectomy</div><div><br/></div><div>REFERENCE:</div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;-en-paragraph:true;"><br clear="none" /></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div>1. Right hemicolectomy specimen: terminal ileum (_ cm in length and _ cm in circumference), ascending colon (_ cm in length and _ cm in circumference), appendix (_ cm in length and _ cm in diameter) and omentum (_ x _ x _ cm). </div><div>2. Tumor configuration: polypoid, fungating, plague-like, annular, discoid, ulcerative infiltrative, diffuse</div><div>3. Tumor size: _ x _ x _ cm</div><div>4. Tumor location: in the _ ascending colon, _ cm from the ileocecal valve and _ cm from distal margin</div><div>5. Other lesions:</div><div><br/></div><div>* A sessile/ pedunculated polyp (_ cm at greatest dimension) is located _ cm to the tumor and _ cm from the nearest margin.</div><div>Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:</div><div>RA-RD: tumor</div><div>RE: surgical margins</div><div>RF: appendix</div><div>omentum</div><div>RG-RL: regional lymph nodes</div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;-en-paragraph:true;"><br clear="none" /></div><div>MICROSCOPIC FINDINGS:</div><div>A. Tumor histological type: adenocarcinoma</div><div>B. Histological grade: well_moderately_poorly differentiated_undifferentiated</div><div>C. Tumor size: ___ x ___ x ___ cm</div><div>D. Invasion depth:</div><div>Reference: intraepithelial/ invasion of lamina propia (Tis); submucosa (T1); muscularis propria (T2); pericolorectal tissues (T3);</div><div>surface of visceral peritoneum (T4a); directly to other organs or structures (T4b)</div><div>E. Angiolymphatic invasion: present / absent</div><div>F. Perineural invasion: present_absent</div><div>G. Tumor deposits (discontinuous extramural extension): present_absent</div><div>H. Margins:</div><div>   1. Proximal surgical margin: uninvolved, __cm in closest distance/_involved</div><div>   2. Distal surgical margin: uninvolved, __cm in closest distance/_involved</div><div>   3. Radial margin (circumferential radial margin of rectum): uninvolved, __ mm in distance/involved</div><div>(≦ 1 mm in distance)</div><div>   3. Serosal margin status of colon: uninvolved, __ mm in distance. / Involved (less than 1mm in</div><div>distance)</div><div>I. Lymph nodes status:</div><div>   1. Metastasis: detected in ___ of the ___ LNs found</div><div>   2. Extra-capsular spread (ECS): present / absent</div><div>* <font style="color: rgb(255, 0, 0);">The pericolonic fat has been serially re-dissected again. Only _ lymph nodes are identified.</font></div><div>* The specimen has been treated with fat-cleaning solution (ethanol). </div><div>   Only 7 small nodes are identified.</div><div>J. Additional pathologic findings:</div><div>* There are extracellular mucin pools in the main tumor as well as in the metastatic foci, accounting for less than 50% of the tumor.</div><div>The appendix and omentum are _free of tumor.</div><div>K. Tumor Regression Grading S/P CCRT:</div><div>not applicable</div><div>Grade 0 (no regression).</div><div>Grade 1 (minor regression, fibrosis in only 25% or less of the tumor mass).</div><div>Grade 2 (obvious fibrosis in 26% to 50% of the tumor mass).</div><div>Grade 3 (dominant fibrosis outgrowing of 50% the tumor mass).</div><div>Grade 4 (total regression, no viable tumor mass, only fibrosis).</div><div><br/></div><div>IMMUNOHISTOCHEMICAL STUDY: (Staining on section   )</div><div>1. EGFR (Novocastra Laboratories, clone: 25 ): weak / moderate / strong cytoplasmic staining in ___to ___% cells and weak / moderate / strong membranous staining in___  to ____%.</div><div><br/></div><div>2. IHC Testing for Mismatch Repair (MMR) Proteins</div><div>a. MLH1: intact nuclear expression</div><div>b. MSH2: intact nuclear expression</div><div>c. MSH6: intact nuclear expression</div><div>d. PMS2: intact nuclear expression</div><div><br/></div><div>loss of nuclear expression</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
