    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Diverticulitis with perforation, _,</div><div>*Harmann procedure and drainage of intra-abdominal abscess</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div>Received is a segment of intestine measuring _ cm in length and _ cm in circumference. There is perforation, located _ cm from the nearest surgical cut end, with induration of wall. The reciprocal external surface shows fibrous adhesion and is coated with purulent exudates. Diverticulae are seen, measuring _ cm at greatest dimension.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div><br/></div><div>    Transmural necrosis and <span style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">architecture</span></span>destruction with replacement by granulation tissue are seen. The adjacent subserosal tissue also reveals fibrosis and aucte and chronic inflammatory cell infiltration.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Sections show a diverticulum with marked inflammatory infiltrate, destruction of the architecture and granulation tissue formation with scattered multinucleated giant cells, extending to the pericolonic fat along with fibrinopurulent coating at subserosal areas. Other diverticulae revealing mixed inflammatory infiltrate near base</div><div>of diverticulae are also seen. No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>小腸破掉</div><div>Sections taken from the perforative site shows hemorrhage throughout the intestinal wall with edematous change and congestion of the lamina propria, admixed with scattered neutrophils. No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div><div style="margin-bottom:16px;"><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Colon_adenoCA_rt hemi ajcc8</title>
    <created>20180105T004724Z</created>
    <updated>20180508T103831Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; line-height: 1.45;">Diagnosis:</span></div><div style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;"></div><div><br/></div><div style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;"></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Gross Description:</span></div><ol><li>Right hemicolectomy specimen: terminal ileum (_ cm in length and _ cm in circumference), ascending colon (_ cm in length and _ cm in circumference), appendix (_ cm in length and _ cm in diameter) and omentum (_ x _ x _ cm). </li><li>Tumor configuration: polypoid, fungating, plague-like, annular, discoid, ulcerative infiltrative, diffuse</li><li>Tumor size: _ x _ x _ cm</li><li>Tumor location: in the _ ascending colon, _ cm from the ileocecal valve and _ cm from distal margin</li><li>Macroscopic Tumor Perforation: Not identified/Present </li><li>A sessile/ pedunculated polyp (_ cm at greatest dimension) is located _ cm to the tumor and _ cm from the nearest margin.</li></ol><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;"></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Sections are taken and labeled as:</span></div><div style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;"></div><div style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;"></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic Description:</span></div><ol><li><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Histologic Type </span></li></ol><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Adenocarcinoma</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Mucinous adenocarcinoma</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Signet-ring cell carcinoma </span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Neuroendocrine carcinoma </span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Squamous cell carcinoma</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Adenosquamous carcinoma</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Undifferentiated carcinoma </span></div><ol start="2"><li><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Histologic Grade </span></li></ol><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">G1: Well differentiated</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">G2: Moderately differentiated</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">G3: Poorly differentiated</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">G4: Undifferentiated</span></div><div style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;"></div><ol start="3"><li><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Tumor Extension</span></li></ol><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">No evidence of primary tumor</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">No invasion (high-grade dysplasia)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Tumor invades lamina propria/muscularis mucosae (intramucosal carcinoma)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Tumor invades submucosa</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Tumor invades muscularis propria</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Tumor invades through the muscularis propria into pericolorectal tissue</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Tumor invades the visceral peritoneum (including tumor continuous with serosal surface through area of inflammation)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Tumor directly invades adjacent structures (specify: __________________)</span></div><div style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;"></div><ol start="4"><li><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Margins </span></li></ol><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Proximal margin: Uninvolved/Involved</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Distal margin: Uninvolved/Involved</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Radial or Mesenteric Margin: Uninvolved/Involved</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">                Distance of tumor from margin:    mm  </span></div><ol start="5"><li><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Lymphovascular Invasion: Not identified/Present </span></li><li><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Perineural Invasion: Not identified/Present</span></li></ol><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">7. *Tumor Budding</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Number of tumor buds in 1 “hotspot” field (specify total number in area=0.785 mm2)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Low score (0-4)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Intermediate score (5-9)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">High score (10 or more)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Cannot be determined</span></div><ol start="8"><li><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">*Type of Polyp in Which Invasive Carcinoma Arose:_________  </span></li><li><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Tumor Deposits: Not identified/Present</span></li></ol><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Specify number of deposits: ____</span></div><ol start="10"><li><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Regional Lymph Nodes</span></li></ol><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"> Number of Lymph Nodes Involved/Examined:</span></div><div style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;"></div><ol start="11"><li><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Pathologic Stage Classification (pTNM, AJCC 8th Edition)  </span></li></ol><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">TNM Descriptors (required only if applicable) (select all that apply)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">m (multiple primary tumors)    r (recurrent)    y (posttreatment)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><br/></span></div><div>K. Tumor Regression Grading S/P CCRT:</div><div>not applicable</div><div>Grade 0 (no regression).</div><div>Grade 1 (minor regression, fibrosis in only 25% or less of the tumor mass).</div><div>Grade 2 (obvious fibrosis in 26% to 50% of the tumor mass).</div><div>Grade 3 (dominant fibrosis outgrowing of 50% the tumor mass).</div><div>Grade 4 (total regression, no viable tumor mass, only fibrosis).</div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><br/></span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">*Additional Pathologic Findings (select all that apply)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><br/></span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Primary Tumor (pT)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pT0: No evidence of primary tumor</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pTis: Carcinoma in situ, intramucosal carcinoma (involvement of lamina propria with no extension through muscularis mucosae)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pT1: Tumor invades the submucosa (through the muscularis mucosa but not into the muscularis propria)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pT2: Tumor invades the muscularis propria</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pT3: Tumor invades through the muscularis propria into pericolorectal tissues</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pT4: Tumor invades the visceral peritoneum or invades or adheres to adjacent organ or structure</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pT4a: Tumor invades through the visceral peritoneum (including gross perforation of the bowel through tumor and continuous invasion of tumor through areas of inflammation to the surface of the visceral peritoneum)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pT4b: Tumor directly invades or adheres to adjacent organs or structures</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Regional Lymph Nodes (pN)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pN0: No regional lymph node metastasis</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pN1: One to three regional lymph nodes are positive (tumor in lymph nodes measuring ≥0.2 mm), or any number of tumor deposits are present and all identifiable lymph nodes are negative</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pN1a: One regional lymph node is positive</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pN1b: Two or three regional lymph nodes are positive</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pN1c: No regional lymph nodes are positive, but there are tumor deposits in the subserosa, mesentery, or nonperitonealized pericolic, or perirectal/mesorectal tissues.</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pN2: Four or more regional lymph nodes are positive</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pN2a: Four to six regional lymph nodes are positive</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pN2b: Seven or more regional lymph nodes are positive</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">ITCs (Isolated tumor cells):0.2mm or less</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Micrometastasis:0.2mm~2mm (當Meta不用特別寫是micrometastasis)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Distant Metastasis (pM)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">M1:  Metastasis to one or more distant sites or organs or peritoneal metastasis is identified   </span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pM1a: Metastasis to one site or organ is identified without peritoneal metastasis</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pM1b: Metastasis to two or more sites or organs is identified without peritoneal metastasis</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pM1c: Metastasis to the peritoneal surface is identified alone or with other site or organ metastases</span></div><div style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;"></div><ol start="12"><li><br/></li><ol><li><br/></li></ol></ol><div style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;"></div></div><div><br style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;" /></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Colon_adenoCA_segmental ajcc8</title>
    <created>20180105T004724Z</created>
    <updated>20180508T103802Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; line-height: 1.45;">Diagnosis:</span></div><div style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;"></div><div><br/></div><div style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;"></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Gross Description:</span></div><ol><li>Segment of colon: __ cm in length and __ cm in circumference</li><li>Tumor configuration: polypoid, fungating, plague-like, discoid, annular, ulcerative infiltrative, diffuse</li><li>Tumor size: _ x _ x _ cm</li><li>Tumor location: ___cm from the surgical margin and _ cm from the other surgical margin</li><li>Other specimen: Two colonic rings are seen, measuring _ cm and _ cm in diameter, respectively.</li><li><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Macroscopic Tumor Perforation: Not identified/Present </span></li><li>* A sessile/ pedunculated polyp (_ cm at greatest dimension) is located _ cm to the tumor and _ cm from the nearest margin.</li></ol><div><br/></div><div style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;"></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Sections are taken and labeled as:</span></div><div><br/></div><div style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;"></div><div style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;"></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic Description:</span></div><ol><li><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Histologic Type </span></li></ol><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Adenocarcinoma</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Mucinous adenocarcinoma</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Signet-ring cell carcinoma </span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Neuroendocrine carcinoma </span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Squamous cell carcinoma</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Adenosquamous carcinoma</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Undifferentiated carcinoma </span></div><ol start="2"><li><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Histologic Grade </span></li></ol><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">G1: Well differentiated</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">G2: Moderately differentiated</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">G3: Poorly differentiated</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">G4: Undifferentiated</span></div><div style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;"></div><ol start="3"><li><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Tumor Extension</span></li></ol><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">No evidence of primary tumor</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">No invasion (high-grade dysplasia)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Tumor invades lamina propria/muscularis mucosae (intramucosal carcinoma)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Tumor invades submucosa</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Tumor invades muscularis propria</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Tumor invades through the muscularis propria into pericolorectal tissue</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Tumor invades the visceral peritoneum (including tumor continuous with serosal surface through area of inflammation)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Tumor directly invades adjacent structures (specify: __________________)</span></div><div style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;"></div><ol start="4"><li><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Margins </span></li></ol><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Proximal margin: Uninvolved/Involved</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Distal margin: Uninvolved/Involved</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Radial or Mesenteric Margin: Uninvolved/Involved</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">                Distance of tumor from margin:    mm  </span></div><ol start="5"><li><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Lymphovascular Invasion: Not identified/Present </span></li><li><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Perineural Invasion: Not identified/Present</span></li></ol><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">7. *Tumor Budding</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Number of tumor buds in 1 “hotspot” field (specify total number in area=0.785 mm2)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Low score (0-4)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Intermediate score (5-9)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">High score (10 or more)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Cannot be determined</span></div><ol start="8"><li><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">*Type of Polyp in Which Invasive Carcinoma Arose:_________  </span></li><li><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Tumor Deposits: Not identified/Present</span></li></ol><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Specify number of deposits: ____</span></div><ol start="10"><li><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Regional Lymph Nodes</span></li></ol><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"> Number of Lymph Nodes Involved/Examined:</span></div><div style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;"></div><ol start="11"><li><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Pathologic Stage Classification (pTNM, AJCC 8th Edition)  </span></li></ol><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">TNM Descriptors (required only if applicable) (select all that apply)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">m (multiple primary tumors)    r (recurrent)    y (posttreatment)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><br/></span></div><div>K. Tumor Regression Grading S/P CCRT:</div><div>not applicable</div><div>Grade 0 (no regression).</div><div>Grade 1 (minor regression, fibrosis in only 25% or less of the tumor mass).</div><div>Grade 2 (obvious fibrosis in 26% to 50% of the tumor mass).</div><div>Grade 3 (dominant fibrosis outgrowing of 50% the tumor mass).</div><div>Grade 4 (total regression, no viable tumor mass, only fibrosis).</div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><br/></span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><br/></span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Primary Tumor (pT)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pT0: No evidence of primary tumor</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pTis: Carcinoma in situ, intramucosal carcinoma (involvement of lamina propria with no extension through muscularis mucosae)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pT1: Tumor invades the submucosa (through the muscularis mucosa but not into the muscularis propria)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pT2: Tumor invades the muscularis propria</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pT3: Tumor invades through the muscularis propria into pericolorectal tissues</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pT4: Tumor invades the visceral peritoneum or invades or adheres to adjacent organ or structure</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pT4a: Tumor invades through the visceral peritoneum (including gross perforation of the bowel through tumor and continuous invasion of tumor through areas of inflammation to the surface of the visceral peritoneum)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pT4b: Tumor directly invades or adheres to adjacent organs or structures</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Regional Lymph Nodes (pN)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pN0: No regional lymph node metastasis</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pN1: One to three regional lymph nodes are positive (tumor in lymph nodes measuring ≥0.2 mm), or any number of tumor deposits are present and all identifiable lymph nodes are negative</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pN1a: One regional lymph node is positive</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pN1b: Two or three regional lymph nodes are positive</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pN1c: No regional lymph nodes are positive, but there are tumor deposits in the subserosa, mesentery, or nonperitonealized pericolic, or perirectal/mesorectal tissues.</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pN2: Four or more regional lymph nodes are positive</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pN2a: Four to six regional lymph nodes are positive</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pN2b: Seven or more regional lymph nodes are positive</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">ITCs (Isolated tumor cells):0.2mm or less</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Micrometastasis:0.2mm~2mm (當Meta不用特別寫是micrometastasis)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Distant Metastasis (pM)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">M1:  Metastasis to one or more distant sites or organs or peritoneal metastasis is identified   </span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pM1a: Metastasis to one site or organ is identified without peritoneal metastasis</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pM1b: Metastasis to two or more sites or organs is identified without peritoneal metastasis</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pM1c: Metastasis to the peritoneal surface is identified alone or with other site or organ metastases</span></div><div style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;"></div><ol start="12"><li><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">*Additional Pathologic Findings (select all that apply)</span></li></ol><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">None identified</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Adenoma(s)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Ulcerative colitis</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Crohn disease</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Diverticulosis</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Dysplasia arising in inflammatory bowel disease</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Other polyps (type[s]): ___________________________</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Other (specify): ___________________________</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">13.</span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"> </span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">*Ancillary Studies </span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">14</span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">. *Comment(s</span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">)</span></div><div style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;"></div></div><div><br style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;" /></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>DCIS_ajcc8</title>
    <created>20180117T075634Z</created>
    <updated>20180502T070934Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt;">DIAGNOSIS:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt;">Ductal carcinoma in situ (T ), _ breast, OP____</span></div><div><font face="Times New Roman" style="font-size: 10pt;"><br/></font></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt;">REFERENCE:</span></div><div><font face="Times New Roman" style="font-size: 10pt;"><br/></font></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt;">GROSS DESCRIPTION:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt;">1. Breast (_ x _ x _ cm and _ gm) with overlying skin _and nipple_(_ x _ cm) and axillary fat (_ x _ x _ cm).</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt;">2. Tumor size: _ x _ x _ cm.</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt;">3. Tumor location: _ o'clock direction, _ cm to the nipple. (according to clinical information)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt;">4. Margin distance:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt;">- Base margin: _ cm</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt;">- Nearest lateral margin: _ cm</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt;">5. Other quadrants: unremarkable.</span></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><font face="Times New Roman" style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 1.45;">Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:</span><br/></font></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><font face="Times New Roman" style="font-size: 10pt;"><br clear="none" /></font></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt;">MICROSCOPIC FINDING:</span></div><ol start="2" style="margin-top: 0mm; margin-bottom: 0mm; margin-left: 0mm; padding-left: 0pt; list-style-type: lower-roman;"><li style="margin-left: 33pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 7pt; text-indent: 0pt;"><span style="color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt;">Histologic type</span></li><li style="margin-left: 33pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 7pt; text-indent: 0pt;"><span style="color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt;">Tumor size (mm):</span></li><li style="margin-left: 33pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 7pt; text-indent: 0pt;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-weight: bold;">Nuclear grade:</span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-weight: bold;">1 /2 /3</span></li><li style="margin-left: 33pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 7pt; text-indent: 0pt;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-weight: bold;">Architectural pattern:</span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-weight: bold;">Comedo / Non-comedo</span></li><li style="margin-left: 33pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 7pt; text-indent: 0pt;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-weight: bold;">Tumor necrosis:</span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-weight: bold;">Absent / Present</span></li></ol><div><span style="text-indent: 0pt;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt;">Microcalcifications:</span></span></div><div><span style="text-indent: 0pt;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt;">Skin:</span></span></div><div><span style="text-indent: 0pt;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt;">Nipple: </span></span></div><div><span style="text-indent: 0pt;"><font face="Times New Roman" style="font-size: 10pt;"><br/></font></span></div><div><font face="Times New Roman" style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="text-indent: 0pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.45;">. Margins:</span><br/></font></div><div style="margin: 0mm 0mm 0mm 7mm; text-indent: 0mm; min-height: 18pt;"><span style="text-indent: 0mm; min-height: 18pt;"><span style="color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt;">Negative, Closest margin (_______ mm from _______ margin)</span></span></div><div style="margin: 0mm 0mm 0mm 7mm; text-indent: 0mm; min-height: 18pt;"><span style="text-indent: 0mm; min-height: 18pt;"><span style="color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt;">Positive (_______ margin)</span></span></div><div><span style="text-indent: 0pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.45;">. Nodal status:</span> <span style="text-indent: 0pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.45;">Negative /Positive (if lymph nodes are present in the specimen)</span><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt;"><br/></span></div><div style="margin: 0mm 0mm 0mm 7mm; text-indent: 0mm; min-height: 18pt;"><span style="text-indent: 0mm; min-height: 18pt;"><span style="color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt;">No. examined: _______</span></span></div><div style="margin: 0mm 0mm 0mm 7mm; text-indent: 0mm; min-height: 18pt;"><span style="text-indent: 0mm; min-height: 18pt;"><span style="color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt;">No. macrometastases (>2 mm): _____</span></span></div><div style="margin: 0mm 0mm 0mm 7mm; text-indent: 0mm; min-height: 18pt;"><span style="text-indent: 0mm; min-height: 18pt;"><span style="color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt;">No. micrometastases (>0.2 ~ 2 mm and/or >200 cells): _____</span></span></div><div style="margin: 0mm 0mm 0mm 7mm; text-indent: 0mm; min-height: 18pt;"><span style="text-indent: 0mm; min-height: 18pt;"><span style="color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt;">No. isolated tumor cells (≤0.2 mm and ≤200 cells): _____</span></span></div><div><span style="text-indent: 0pt;"><span style="color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.45; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt;">. Treatment Effect: Not applicable</span></span></div><div><span style="text-indent: 0pt;"><span style="color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.45; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt;">. </span></span></div><div><font face="Times New Roman" style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="text-indent: 0pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.45;">. Immunohistochemical Study</span><br/></font></div><ol style="margin-top: 0mm; margin-bottom: 0mm; margin-left: 0mm; padding-left: 0pt; list-style-type: lower-roman;"><li style="margin-left: 36pt; margin-right: 0pt; text-indent: 0pt;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-weight: bold;">ER (Ab):</span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-weight: bold;">Positive /Negative (  %</span><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(255, 0, 0); font-weight: bold;">*, weak / moderate / strong</span><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-weight: bold;">)</span></li><li style="margin-left: 36pt; margin-right: 0pt; text-indent: 0pt;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-weight: bold;">PR (Ab):</span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-weight: bold;">Positive /Negative (  %</span><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(255, 0, 0); font-weight: bold;">*, weak / moderate / strong</span><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-weight: bold;">)</span></li><li style="margin-left: 36pt; margin-right: 0pt; text-indent: 0pt;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-weight: bold;">Her-2/neu (Ab):</span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-weight: bold;">Positive (3+) /Equivocal (2+) /Negative (1+/0)</span></li></ol><div style="page-break-before: always;margin-top:1em;margin-bottom:1em;-en-paragraph:true;"></div><div><span style="min-height: 18pt;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt;"> </span></span></div></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Esophagus</title>
    <created>20151110T070538Z</created>
    <updated>20170808T023503Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">DIAGNOSIS:</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">1. Squamous cell carcinoma (pT <span style="text-decoration: underline;">)</span> / status post neoadjuvant CCRT (ypT ) with nodal status ( <span style="text-decoration: underline;">/</span> , pN ), esophagus</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">2. Negative for malignancy, surgical margins / and stomach</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">Esophagectomy</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;"><br clear="none" /></span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">GROSS FINDINGS:</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">A. Specimen Size:<br clear="none" />
- Esophagus: cm in length and cm in diameter.<br clear="none" />
- Stomach: x cm.<br clear="none" />
- Others:<br clear="none" /></span><br clear="none" /></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">B. Tumor location:</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">- Esophagus: esophagogastric junction / upper / middle / lower third;<br clear="none" /><span style="text-decoration: underline;">not</span> involving esophagogastric junction</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">- Gastric tumor (arising from within proximal 5 cm of the stomach) not extends to / just extends to / extends to ___ cm above the esophagogastric junction</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">C. Tumor size:</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">- Solitary tumor: x x cm</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">- Multiple tumor (__ in number): up to ___ x __ x __ cm</span></p></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family:gotham, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;">Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:</span></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">MICROSCOPIC FINDINGS:</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">A. Histological type: squamous cell carcinoma</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">B. Histological grade:</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">___ Not applicable</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">___ GX: Cannot be assessed</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">___ G1: Well differentiated</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">___ G2: Moderately differentiated</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">___ G3: Poorly differentiated</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">___ G4: Undifferentiated</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">C. Tumor size: ___ x __ x __ cm</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">D. Microscopic Tumor Extension (pT):</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">___ cannot be assessed (pTX)</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">___ No evidence of primary tumor (pT0)</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">___ High-grade dysplasia (carcinoma in situ) (pTis)</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">___ Tumor invades lamina propria (pT1a)</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">___ Tumor invades muscularis mucosa (pT1a)</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">___ Tumor invades submucosa (pT1b)</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">___ Tumor invades muscularis propria (pT2)</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">___ Tumor invades adventitia (pT3)</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">___ Tumor directly invades adjacent structures (specify): ________________ (pT4)</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">E. Margins (Distance of invasive carcinoma from closest margin):<br clear="none" />
- Proximal margin: uninvolved ( cm) / involved<br clear="none" />
- Distal margin: uninvolved ( cm) / involved</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">- Circumferential (Adventitial) margin: uninvolved ( cm) / involved</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">F. Lymph-Vascular Invasion: absent/ present</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">G. Perineural invasion: absent/ present</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">I. Treatment Effect (applicable to carcinomas treated with neoadjuvant therapy):</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">___ No prior treatment</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">___ No residual tumor (complete response, grade 0)</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">___ Marked response (grade 1, minimal residual cancer)</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">___ Moderate response (grade 2)</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">___ No definite response identified (grade 3, poor or no response)</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">___ Treatment history not known</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">J. Lymph node status (pN):</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">- Metastasis ( / , pN1: Regional lymph node metastasis involving 1 to 2 nodes / pN2: 3 to 6 nodes involved / pN3: 7 or more nodes involved)</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">- Extra-capsular spread (ECS): absent/ present</span></p></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">K. Distant Metastasis (pM): Not applicable / present (pM1, site: )</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><br/></span></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><br/></span></span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><div><span style="font-size: 16px;"><br clear="none" /></span></div></div><div><span style="font-size: 16px;"><en-media hash="1585eaecaf2e838e458e6356cbd137b4" type="application/pdf" /></span></div><div><br/></div><div><br clear="none" /></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
