  <note>
    <title>FZ SLN+ 後面沒有做</title>
    <created>20200225T042922Z</created>
    <updated>20250507T074708Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Pathological Diagnosis :</div><ol><li><div>Lymph node, sentinel, _ axilla, frozen biopsy ---</div></li></ol><div>   Carcinoma, metastatic.</div><ol start="2"><li><div>Lymph node, non-sentinel, _ axilla, frozen biopsy ---</div></li></ol><div><br/></div><div>Gross description:</div><ol><li><div>SLN #1:The specimen consists of a piece of nodal tissue</div></li></ol><div>measuring _ x _ x _ cm in size.</div><ol start="2"><li><div>SLN #2 The specimen consists of a piece of nodal tissue</div></li></ol><div>measuring _ x _ x _ cm in size.</div><ol start="3"><li><div>Non-SLN #1: The specimen consists of a piece of nodal</div></li></ol><div>tissue measuring _ x _ x _ cm in size.</div><ol start="4"><li><div>Non-SLN #2: The specimen consists of a piece of nodal</div></li></ol><div>tissue measuring _ x _ x _ cm in size.</div><div><br/></div><div>The sentinel lymph nodes are sliced and totally embedded for</div><div>frozen section and then fixed in formalin for paraffin embedding.</div><div>The non-sentinel lymph nodes are fixed in formalin for paraffin embedding.    </div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
