  <note>
    <title>GI_NET</title>
    <created>20170621T075040Z</created>
    <updated>20170621T075042Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>1. Histologic type: neuroendocrine tumor/ neuroendocrine carcinoma</div><div>2. Histological grade: G1/G2/G3</div><div>G1: mitotic count, &lt; 2/10 HPF and/or &lt;or=2% Ki67 index</div><div>G2: mitotic count, 2-20/10 HPF and/or 3-20% Ki67 index</div><div>G3: mitotic count, >20/10 HPF and/or >20% Ki67 index</div><div>3. Tumor size: ___ (greatest dimension) x ___ x ___</div><div>4. Tumor focality: Unifocal/Multifocal (specify number of tumors: ______)</div><div>5. Mitotic Rate:  ___ /10 HPF</div><div>6. Microscopic Tumor Extension   </div><div>___ Cannot be assessed</div><div>___ No evidence of primary tumor</div><div>___ Tumor invades lamina propria</div><div>___ Tumor invades into but not through muscularis mucosae</div><div>___ Tumor invades submucosa</div><div>___ Tumor invades muscularis propria</div><div>___ Tumor invades through the muscularis propria into the subserosal adipose tissue or the nonperitonealized pericolic or perirectal soft tissues but does not extend to the serosal surface (visceral peritoneum) </div><div>___ Tumor penetrates serosa (visceral peritoneum) </div><div>___ Tumor directly invades adjacent structures (specify: ____________________)</div><div>___ Tumor penetrates to the surface of the visceral peritoneum (serosa) and directly invades adjacent structures (specify: ____________________)</div><div>7. Lymphovascular invasion: not identified/ present</div><div>8. Perineural invasion: not identified/ present</div><div>9. Margins: free/ involved; Distance of tumor from closest margin: ___ mm or ___ cm</div><div>10.Ki-67 labeling index: &lt; or=2%/ 3% to 20%/ >20%</div><div>11.Additional Pathologic Findings (select all that apply) </div><div>___ Tumor necrosis</div><div> ___ Other (specify): __________________________</div><div>12.Pathologic staging: pT___N____M____ (according to AJCC 7th).</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>GIST</title>
    <created>20170718T005911Z</created>
    <updated>20251225T020950Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:
Gastrointestinal stromal tumor (GIST).</div><div>MICROSCOPIC EVALUATION:
Tumor:</div><ul><li><div>Type: Gastrointestinal stromal tumor, spindle type _epithelioid type _mixed spindle and epithelioid type</div></li><li><div>Mitosis: _ per 5 square mm (equivalent to conventional 50 HPFs) (NOTE A)</div></li><li><div>Greatest dimension: _ cm</div></li><li><div>Necrosis: Absent  _Present </div></li><li><div>Risk assessment </div><div>Revised NIH risk (2008): _</div><div>AFIP criteria (2006): UICC _ </div><div>TNM stage: pT_</div></li><li><div>Tumor ruptured: Absent _Present</div></li></ul><div>Surgical margins:</div><ul><li><div>Uninvolved, _ cm in distance</div></li><li><div>Involved.</div></li></ul><div> Immunohistochemical studies:</div><ul><li><div>CD117: Positive</div></li><li><div>Dog1: Positive</div></li><li><div>CD34:</div></li><li><div>Smooth muscle actin (SMA):</div></li><li><div>S-100: Negative</div></li><li><div>Desmin:</div></li></ul><div><br/></div><div>NOTE A:
Our 40x lens has working distance of 0.55 mm, thus need 21 HPFs.</div><div><br/></div><div>(This case has been reviewed by two pathologists.)</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>GIST</title>
    <created>20170410T074238Z</created>
    <updated>20231205T031050Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Gastrointestinal stromal tumor (GIST) (pTNM).</div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC FINDING:</div><div>1. Tumor:</div><div>  a. Type: Gastrointestinal stromal tumor, spindle/epithelioid/mixed/other (specify) type</div><div>  b. Mitosis:  per 5 square mm(equivalent to conventional 50 HPFs) (NOTE A)</div><div>                           ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~</div><div>  c. greastest dimension:       cm</div><div>  d. necrosis: present / absent</div><div>  e. risk assessment: Revised NIH risk (2008) :</div><div>                   AFIP criteria (2006) :     UICC</div><div>                   TNM stage：</div><div>  f. tumor ruptured: present / absent</div><div>2. Surgical margins:</div><div>  a. uninvolved, closest _____ margin is __ cm away</div><div>  b. involved the _____ margin</div><div>3. Immunohistochemical studies:</div><div>  a. CD117:</div><div>  b. CD34:</div><div>  c. DOG1:</div><div>  d. S-100:</div><div>  e. Desmin:</div><en-media hash="39e1852efad37fa7a798ee3a7fd60c21" type="application/pdf" /><div>NOTE A:</div><div>Our 40x lens has working distance of 0.55 mm, thus need 21 HPFs.</div><div><span style="font-family: Arial;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">___ pT1: Tumor 2 cm or less</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: Arial;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">___ pT2: Tumor more than 2 cm but not more than 5 cm</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: Arial;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">___ pT3: Tumor more than 5 cm but not more than 10 cm</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: Arial;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">___ pT4: Tumor more than 10 cm in greatest dimension</span></span></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
