  <note>
    <title>HCC ajcc8</title>
    <created>20180108T084145Z</created>
    <updated>20180420T010203Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-url>file:///F:\2015%20大件癌症%20form\修改版-給癌症中心\肝癌.doc</source-url>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><div><div><br/></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">(</span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">含</span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">hepatocellular carcinoma</span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">及</span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">intrahepatic cholangiocarcinoma)</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Diagnosis:</span></div><div>Liver, ___, ___ --- </div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Gross Description:</span></div><ol><li>Procedure</li></ol><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Wedge resection/Atypical hepatectomy</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Right lobectomy/Left lobectomy/segmentectomy</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Total hepatectomy</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Other (specify): ____________________________</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Specimen Size and Weight:</span></div><ol start="2"><li>Tumor Focality: Solitary/Multiple (number:  )</li><li>Tumor Site: Right lob/ Left lobe/ Caudate lobe / Quadrate lobe</li><li>Tumor Size:   x   x     cm</li><li>Satellitosis: Not identified/ Present</li><li>Large vessel involvement: Not identified/ Present</li><li>Non-tumorous part: cirrhotic/ Not cirrhotic</li><li>Gallbladder: size:    x     x     cm.</li></ol><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Gallstone: Not identified/Present</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Sections are taken and labeled as:</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic Description:</span></div><ol><li>Histologic type: Hepatocellular carcinoma</li><li><span style="line-height: 1.45;">Histologic Grade: (According to the Edmondson and Steiner System)</span></li></ol><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">G1: Well differentiated</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">G2: Moderately differentiated</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">G3: Poorly differentiated</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">G4: Undifferentiated</span></div><ol start="3"><li>Tumor Extension </li></ol><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Tumor confined to liver</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Tumor involves a major branch of the portal vein</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Tumor involves hepatic vein(s)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Tumor involves (perforates) visceral peritoneum</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Tumor directly invades gallbladder</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Tumor directly invades diaphragm</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Tumor directly invades other adjacent organs (specify):_______________________</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Tumor growth pattern</span></div><div>Satellite nodule status</div><div>Tumor necrosis: </div><div>Bile duct invasion: Absent</div><div>Tumor capsule status (10): Encapsulation / Partial encapsulation (__%) / Absent</div><div><br/></div><ol start="4"><li>Parenchymal Margin </li></ol><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Uninvolved by invasive carcinoma</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Distance of invasive carcinoma from margin:    cm      </span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Involved by invasive carcinoma</span></div><ol start="5"><li>Vascular Invasion</li></ol><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Not identified</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Present: Small vessel invasion/Large vessel invasion</span></div><ol start="6"><li>＊Perineural Invasion: Not identified/Present</li></ol><div>Treatment effect:</div><div>___ No known presurgical therapy ___ Complete necrosis (no viable tumor) ___ Incomplete necrosis (viable tumor present) + Percentage tumor necrosis: ____% ___ No necrosis ___ Cannot be determined (explain): ____________________________</div><ol start="6"><li>＊Regional Lymph Nodes</li></ol><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">No lymph nodes submitted or found</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Number of lymph nodes involved/examined:    /</span></div><ol start="8"><li>Pathologic Stage Classification (pTNM, AJCC 8th Edition)</li></ol><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Primary Tumor (pT)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pT1: Solitary tumor</span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">&lt;</span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">2 cm, or >2 cm without vascular invasion</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pT1a:       Solitary tumor ≤2 cm</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pT1b:       Solitary tumor >2 cm without vascular invasion</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pT2: Solitary tumor >2 cm with vascular invasion, or multiple tumors, none >5 cm</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pT3: Multiple tumors, at least one of which is >5 cm</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pT4: Single tumor or multiple tumors of any size involving a major branch of the portal vein or hepatic vein, or tumor(s) with direct invasion of adjacent organs other than the gallbladder or with perforation of visceral peritoneum</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Regional Lymph Nodes (pN)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pNX: Regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pN0: No regional lymph node metastasis</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pN1: Regional lymph node metastasis</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Distant Metastasis (pM)</span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">(required only if confirmed pathologically in this case)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pM1: Distant metastasis</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Specify site(s): ____________________________</span></div><ol start="9"><li>Additional Pathologic Findings</li></ol><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">None identified</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Low-grade dysplastic nodule</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">High-grade dysplastic nodule</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Steatosis</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Steatohepatitis</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Chronic hepatitis (specify etiology): ____________________________</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Other (specify): ____________________________</span></div><div><br/></div><ol start="10"><li style="min-height: 13pt;"><span style="min-height: 13pt; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">Cirrhosis (probable or definite) </span></li><li>Gallbladder: No pathologic change/Chronic cholecystitis/Cholelethiasis</li><li>＊Ancillary Studies </li><li>＊Comment(s)</li></ol><div><br/></div></div><ol style="margin-top: 0mm; margin-bottom: 0mm; margin-left: 0mm; padding-left: 0pt;"><li style="margin-left: 15pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 6pt; text-indent: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-weight: bold;">Ishak modified staging of fibrosis</span></li><ol style="list-style-type: none;margin-top: 0mm; margin-bottom: 0mm; margin-left: 0mm; padding-left: 0pt;"><li style="margin-left: 15pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; text-indent: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">0 No fibrosis</span></li><li style="margin-left: 15pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; text-indent: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">1 Fibrous expansion of some portal areas, with or without short fibrous septa</span></li><li style="margin-left: 15pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; text-indent: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">2 Fibrous expansion of most portal areas, with or without short fibrous septa</span></li><li style="margin-left: 15pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; text-indent: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">3 Fibrous expansion of most portal areas with occasional portal to portal bridging</span></li><li style="margin-left: 15pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; text-indent: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">4 Fibrous expansion of portal areas with marked bridging (portal to portal as well as portal to central</span></li><li style="margin-left: 15pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; text-indent: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">5 Marked bridging with occasional nodules (incomplete cirrhosis)</span></li><li style="margin-left: 15pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; text-indent: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">6 Cirrhosis (probable or definite) </span></li></ol></ol></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>IDC_ajcc8</title>
    <created>20180109T073419Z</created>
    <updated>20231214T032455Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Diagnosis</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">Breast, ____, _____ --- (pT)</span></div><div>Axillary lymph nodes, ___, dissection --- Free of metastasis / Metastasis ()</div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Gross Description:</span></div><div>The specimen received is a formalin-fixed breast tissue with overlying skin, including</div><div>nipple and attached axillary content.</div><div>1. Breast (_ x _ x _ cm and _ gm) with overlying skin _and nipple_(_ x _ cm) and axillary fat (_ x _ x _ cm). <span style="line-height: 1.45;">It had been sectioned partially when received.</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">2. Tumor size: _ x _ x _ cm.</span></div><div>3. Tumor location:  _ o'clock position of the breast, _ cm from the nipple * (according to clinical information)</div><div>4. Margin distance: _ cm from the base; _ cm from the lateral margin.</div><div>5. Other quadrants: unremarkable.</div><div><br style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;" /></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Sections are taken and labeled as:</span></div><div><br style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;" /></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic Description</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">- Histologic type: </span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">Invasive ductal carcinoma/ Invasive lobular carcinoma/____________</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">- Size of invasive carcinoma (mm):</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">- Histologic grade (Nottingham histologic score):</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">Grade I (score 3-5) / grade II (score 6,7) /grade III (score 8,9)</span></div><div>- Tubule formation: score 1/ 2/ 3</div><div>- Nuclear pleomorphism: score 1/ 2/ 3</div><div>- Mitotic count: score 1/ 2/ 3</div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">- Extensive intraductal component: absent/ present, comedo/non-comedo type</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">Ductal carcinoma in situ component: _, comedo type_cribriform pattern</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">*present within the tumor though not >25% of the whole tumorous area</span></div><div>- Extent of tumor (required only if the structures are present and involved)</div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">Skin involvement: Absent / Present (without ulceration / with ulceration / macroscopically satellite skin foci)</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">Chest wall invasion deeper than pectoralis muscle: Absent / Present</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">- Nipple: free/Paget's disease</span></div><div>- Peritumor lymphatic/vascular invasion: present/not identified</div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">- Margins:</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;"> Negative, Closest margin (_______ mm from _______ margin)</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">Positive (_______ margin)</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">- Nodal status: Negative /Positive (if lymph nodes are present in the specimen)</span></div><div>*, compiled from the report of sentinel lymph node biopsy (201_-_-_)</div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">No. examined: _______</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">No. macrometastases (>2 mm): _____</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">No. micrometastases (>0.2 ~ 2 mm and/or >200 cells): _____</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">No. isolated tumor cells (&lt;=0.2 mm and &lt;=200 cells): _____</span></div><div>Extranodal extension: Absent Present</div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">- Treatment Effect: Response to presurgical (neoadjuvant) therapy (if patient received)</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">In the Breast</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">No definite response to presurgical therapy in the invasive carcinoma</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">Probable or definite response to presurgical therapy in the invasive carcinoma</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">No residual invasive carcinoma is present in the breast after presurgical therapy</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">In the Lymph nodes</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">No lymph nodes removed</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">No definite response to presurgical therapy in metastatic carcinoma</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">Probable or definite response to presurgical therapy in metastatic carcinoma</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">No lymph node metastases. Fibrous scarring, possibly related to prior lymph node metastases with pathologic complete response</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">No lymph node metastases and no prominent fibrous scarring in the nodes</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">- Immunohistochemical Study</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">ER (Ab): Positive /Negative (  %, weak / moderate / strong)</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">PR (Ab): Positive /Negative (  %, weak / moderate / strong)</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">Her-2/neu (Ab): Positive (3+) /Equivocal (2+) /Negative (1+/0)</span></div><div>Ki-67</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Intestine (adhesion)</title>
    <created>20161114T010930Z</created>
    <updated>20240229T085814Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Small intestine, resection --- Fibrosis.</div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div>Received is a segment of intestine with severe adhesion between small bowel loop. The</div><div>intestine measures about _ cm in length and _ cm in diameter.</div><div><br/></div><div>Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:</div><div>RA-RD: intestine</div><div>RE: bilateral margins</div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC FINDING:</div><div>Sections show prominent fibrosis, vascular congestion and presence of fibrinopurulent</div><div>coating on serosal site. _ lymph nodes are seen with preserved nodal architecture. No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Intrahepatic cholangiocarcinoma ajcc8</title>
    <created>20180109T080626Z</created>
    <updated>20260420T135052Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Diagnosis: </div><div>Liver, S_, procedure --- <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Intrahepatic cholangiocarcinoma (pT_)</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Lymph nodes, regional, dissection --- No metastasis (0/_, pN0) / Carcinoma, metastatic (_/_, pN_)</span></span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Gross Description:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">1.     Procedure:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">    Wedge resection/Atypical hepatectomy</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">    Right lobectomy/Left lobectomy/segmentectomy</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Total hepatectomy</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">2.     Tumor Focality:</span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Solitary/Multiple (number:  )</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">3.     Tumor Site:</span> </div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">4.     Tumor Size:  _ x _ x _ cm</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">5.     Non-tumorous part:</span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">cirrhotic/ Not cirrhotic</span></div><ol start="6"><li><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Margin: </span></div></li></ol><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">7.     Gallbladder:</span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">size: _ x _ x _ cm; wall thickness: _ cm</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">    Gallstone: Not identified/Present</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Sections are taken and labeled as:</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic Description:</span></div><div>Histologic Type:</div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ Large duct intrahepatic cholangiocarcinoma</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ Small duct intrahepatic cholangiocarcinoma</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ Cholangiocarcinoma, NOS</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ Combined hepatocellular-cholangiocarcinoma</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ Intraductal papillary neoplasm with associated invasive carcinoma</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ Intraductal tubulopapillary neoplasm with associated invasive carcinoma</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ Mucinous cystic neoplasm with associated invasive carcinoma</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ Undifferentiated carcinoma, NOS</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ Large cell neuroendocrine carcinoma</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ Small cell neuroendocrine carcinoma</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ High-grade neuroendocrine carcinoma</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ Mixed neuroendocrine-non-neuroendocrine neoplasm (MiNEN) (specify component): ___</span></span></div><div>Histologic Grade: </div><div>_G1: Well differentiated</div><div>_G2: Moderately differentiated</div><div>_G3: Poorly differentiated</div><div>Tumor Size: _ cm in greatest dimension</div><div>Tumor Growth Pattern</div><div><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ Mass-forming</span></div><div><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ Periductal infiltrating</span></div><div><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ Mixed mass-forming and periductal infiltrating</span></div><div>Tumor Extension  </div><div><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ Confined to hepatic parenchyma</span></div><div><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ Involves visceral peritoneal surface</span></div><div><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ Directly invades gallbladder</span></div><div><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ Directly invades adjacent structure(s) and organ(s) other than gallbladder</span></div><div><b><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Margin status for invasive carcinoma:
- </span></b>Parenchymal margin:</div><div>_Uninvolved by invasive carcinoma, _ cm in distance     
_Involved by invasive carcinoma</div><div>_&lt;1 mm</div><div>- Bile duct margin:</div><div>_Uninvolved by invasive carcinoma, _ cm in distance     
_Involved by invasive carcinoma</div><div>_&lt;1 mm</div><div>Margin status for high-grade intraepithelial neoplasia: </div><div>___ All margins negative for high-grade intraepithelial neoplasia
___ High-grade intraepithelial neoplasia present at bile duct margin</div><div><b><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Lymphatic and / or Vascular Invasion</span></b></div><div><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ Not identified</span></div><div><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ Present</span></div><div>Perineural Invasion: Not identified/Present</div><div>Regional Lymph Nodes</div><div>_No lymph nodes submitted or found</div><div>_Number of lymph nodes involved/examined: _/_</div><div><b><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Treatment effect:</span></b></div><div><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ No known presurgical therapy</span></div><div><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ Present, with no viable cancer cells (complete response, score 0)</span></div><div><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ Present, with single cells or rare small groups of cancer cells (near complete response, score 1)</span></div><div><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ Present, with residual cancer showing evident tumor regression, but more than single cells or rare</span></div><div><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">small groups of cancer cells (partial response, score 2)</span></div><div><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ Present, NOS</span></div><div><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ Absent, with extensive residual cancer and no evident tumor regression (poor or no response, score 3)</span></div><div>Additional Pathologic Findings:</div><div>None identified / Low-grade dysplastic nodule / High-grade dysplastic nodule /  Steatosis / Steatohepatitis / Chronic hepatitis (specify etiology):</div><div>Fibrosis (Ishak score): [demonstrated by Masson's trichrome]</div><div>_0 No fibrosis</div><div>_1 Fibrous expansion of some portal areas, with or without short fibrous septa</div><div>_2 Fibrous expansion of most portal areas, with or without short fibrous septa</div><div>_3 Fibrous expansion of most portal areas with occasional portal to portal  bridging</div><div>_4 Fibrous expansion of portal areas with marked bridging (portal to portal as  well as portal to central</div><div>_5 Marked bridging with occasional nodules (incomplete cirrhosis)</div><div>_6 Cirrhosis (probable or definite)</div><div>Gallbladder: No pathologic change/ Chronic cholecystitis with cholelethiasis</div><div><span style="font-family: Calibri;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:#010101;">pTNM:  pT___N___ (AJCC cancer staging system, 8th edition)</span></span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: Calibri;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:#010101;">TNM descriptors: not applicable; ___y(posttherapy); ___r(retreatment); ___a(autopsy); ___m(multiple);  </span></span></span></div><div><br/></div><div>(This case has been peer reviewed by two doctors.)</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>John 的 Gross 2015/10</title>
    <created>20151016T080011Z</created>
    <updated>20160805T030144Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div><br clear="none" />GROSS FINDINGS<br clear="none" />The specimen consists of three wedge resections of lung, each with a stapled edge, arbitrarily designated wedges 1, 2 and 3.<br clear="none" />Wedge 1: Measures 28 x 14 x 5 mm, weight 1.0g, pleura intact. Cut surface is variegated, brown to black without distinct lesions.<br clear="none" />Wedge 2: Measures 33 x 7 x 7 mm, weight 0.5g, pleura intact. Cut surface is variegated, brown to black without distinct lesions.<br clear="none" />Wedge 3: Measures 39 x 10 x 5 mm, weight 1.5g, pleura intact. Cut surface shows a solitary black nodule 5 mm in maximum dimension.<br clear="none" /><br clear="none" />The specimen is all embedded.<br clear="none" />AA: Wedge 1.<br clear="none" />AB: Wedge 2.<br clear="none" />AC: Wedge 3 nodule.<br clear="none" />AD: Wedge 3 remaining tissue.<br clear="none" /><br clear="none" />559 <br clear="none" /><br clear="none" />GROSS FINDINGS<br clear="none" />The specimen consists of a piece of mucosa with submucosa measuring 19 x 15 x 6 mm. The mucosal surface is normal without discrete lesions. The cut surface shows a poorly defined grey to brown, spongy area measuring 9 x 9 x 6 mm which extends to the margin.<br clear="none" /><br clear="none" />The specimen is all embedded.<br clear="none" />AA-AB: All tissue embedded. <br clear="none" /><br clear="none" />561<br clear="none" /><br clear="none" />GROSS FINDINGS<br clear="none" />A. Liver specimen (wedge resection of segments VI and VII) <br clear="none" />Segment VI and VII composite: 84 x 73 x 53 mm and 140.0 g <br clear="none" />It had been incised partially when received.<br clear="none" />B. Tumor: Solitary <br clear="none" />Segment VI and VII composite: White to cream, 55 x 50 x 47 mm; capsule intact; necrosis 5% <br clear="none" />C. Tumor-free resection margin (in the nearest tumor): 7 mm <br clear="none" />D. Large vessel (venous) invasion: Not identified <br clear="none" />E. Non-tumorous liver: Non-cirrhotic<br clear="none" /><br clear="none" />Representative sections are taken.<br clear="none" />RA-RB: Tumour to resection margin.<br clear="none" />RC-RD: Tumour to overlying capsule, including necrotic area.<br clear="none" />RE: Additional section of tumour to capsule.<br clear="none" />RF: Uninvolved liver.<br clear="none" /><br clear="none" />563<br clear="none" /><br clear="none" />GROSS FINDINGS<br clear="none" />1. [Esophago-gastric junction] The specimen consists of a segment of distal oesophagus and a segment of proximal stomach, submitted as separate pieces and are described separately.<br clear="none" />Esophagus: 123 mm long x 37 mm in diameter. On opening, a poorly defined erythematous, possibly ulcerated area is seen at the mid section, measuring 35 x 32 mm. This is 49 mm from the proximal (true) margin and 40 mm from the distal (false) margin. There is no obvious tumour seen and on sectioning through the wall there are no lesions identified. 50% of this area is embedded. No lymph nodes are identified within the paraesophageal soft tissue. The proximal (true) margin is inked green and the distal (false) margin is left uninked.<br clear="none" />Stomach: 109 x 47 x 24 mm. On opening, no lesions are seen on the mucosal surface. A small slip of normal esophageal squamous mucosa is noted at the proximal aspect. Several lymph nodes are identified in the lesser curve fat, measuring up to 8 mm in diameter. One lymph node is suspicious for tumour involvement. The proximal (false) margin is left uninked and the distal (true) margin is inked green.<br clear="none" />2. [Paraesophageal LN] The specimen consists of multiple fragments of lymph node tissue and fat measuring from 1-8 mm in maximum dimension. <br clear="none" />3. [Subcarinal LN] The specimen consists of four fragments of lymph node tissue and fat measuring from 5-9 mm in maximum dimension. <br clear="none" />4. [Pulmonary ligament LN] The specimen consists of three fragments of lymph node tissue and fat measuring from 2-11 mm in maximum dimension. <br clear="none" />5. [Cervical LN] The specimen consists of three fragments of lymph node tissue and fat measuring from 3-12 mm in maximum dimension. <br clear="none" />6. [Lesser curve LN] The specimen consists of a piece of fat measuring 26 x 14 x 3 mm. No obvious lymph node is seen.<br clear="none" />7. [Celiac axis LN] The specimen consists of a single lymph node measuring 31 x 27 x 23 mm. The cut surface shows the node has been replaced by necrotic tumour. <br clear="none" /><br clear="none" />Representative sections are taken.<br clear="none" />RA: True proximal (esophageal) and distal (gastric) margins.<br clear="none" />RB-RE: Representative sections of erythematous area (50% embedded).<br clear="none" />RF: Gastroesophageal junction.<br clear="none" />RG: 1x lesser curve lymph node with possible tumour.<br clear="none" />RH: 3x lesser curve lymph nodes.<br clear="none" />RI: 2x lesser curve lymph nodes.<br clear="none" />AJ: Paraesophageal LN.<br clear="none" />AK: Subcarinal LN.<br clear="none" />AL: Pulmonary ligament LN.<br clear="none" />AM: Cervical LN.<br clear="none" />AN: Lesser curve LN.<br clear="none" />RO: Celiac axis LN, representative section.<br clear="none" /><br clear="none" />566<br clear="none" /><br clear="none" />GROSS FINDINGS<br clear="none" />1. [Left ovary] The specimen consists of a disrupted cystic ovary with attached fallopian tube, weighing 132.5 g in aggregate. The ovary measures 127 x 78 x 63 mm, and the fallopian tube measures 47 mm in length and 7 mm in diameter. The cut surface of the ovary has a simple, oligocystic appearance with abundant attached blood clot and fibrin debris. The wall measures up to 6 mm in thickness and on sectioning shows a small intramural region with a mucinous appearance; there are otherwise no suspicious areas. The cut surface of the fallopian tube shows no obvious lesions.<br clear="none" />2. [Right ovary] The specimen consists of a heavily calcified ovary measuring 37 x 28 x 24 mm and weighing 16 g. The calcification precludes sectioning and the tissue is submitted for decalcification prior to sampling.<br clear="none" /><br clear="none" />Representative sections are taken.<br clear="none" />RA-RE: Left ovary, with C including mucinous appearing area.<br clear="none" />RF: Left fallopian tube.<br clear="none" />RG-RH: Right ovary (post decalcification).</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
