    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Renal cell carcinoma (pT ) with/ without regional lymph node metastasis ( / N ) unassessable nodal status (pNx), right/ left kidney and ureter,</div><p><br clear="none" /></p><div>Nepherectomy<br clear="none" />Nephroureterectomy and _bladder cuff excision<p><br clear="none" /></p><div>REFERENCES:<p><br clear="none" /></p><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:<br clear="none" />1. Nephrectomy specimen: kidney (_ x _ x _ and _ gm) with ureter (_ cm in length, _ cm in diameter ) , adrenal gland (_ x _ x _ ) and bladder cuff (_ x _ x _ cm)<br clear="none" />2. Tumor size: _ x _ x _ cm <br clear="none" />3. Tumor location: _upper pole_lower pole upper with _mild_moderate_severe hydronephroisis <br clear="none" />4. Tumor necrosis: absent/ present<br clear="none" />5. Perinephric tissues:<p><br clear="none" /></p><div>Representative sections are submitted in cassettes:<br clear="none" />R_: tumor of kidney / ureter<br clear="none" />R_: other renal parenchyma<br clear="none" />R_: ureter<br clear="none" />R_: renal pelvis<br clear="none" />R_: hilar vessels<br clear="none" />R_: perirenal fat<p><br clear="none" /></p><div>MICROSCOPIC DESCRIPTION:<br clear="none" />1. Tumor type: clear cell_renal cell carcinoma (RCC)<br clear="none" />2. Nuclear grade: 1/4, 2/4, 3/4, 4/4 ( for RCC )<br clear="none" />3. Growth pattern: acinar/ papillary/ papillary and acinar/ papillary and tubular/solid <br clear="none" />4. Tumor size: _ x _ x _ cm<br clear="none" />5. Tumor stage: <br clear="none" />T1a Tumor 4 cm or less in greatest dimension, limited to the kidney<br clear="none" />T1b Tumor more than 4 cm but not more than 7 cm in greatest dimension limited to<br clear="none" />T2a Tumor more than 7 cm but less than or equal to 10 cm in greatest dimension, limited to the kidney<br clear="none" />T2b Tumor more than 10 cm, limited to the kidney<br clear="none" />T3a Tumor grossly extends into the renal vein or its segmental (muscle containing)branches, or tumor invades perirenal and/or renal sinus fat but not beyond Gerota’s fascia<br clear="none" />T3b Tumor grossly extends into the vena cava below the diaphragm<br clear="none" />T3c Tumor grossly extends into the vena cava above the diaphragm or invades the wall of the vena cava<br clear="none" />T4 Tumor invades beyond Gerota’s fascia (including contiguous extension into the<br clear="none" /> ipsilateral adrenal gland)<br clear="none" />6. Renal vein invasion: absent _present<br clear="none" />7. Surgical margins: free/ involves the ureteral margin / bladder cuff<br clear="none" />8. Adrenal gland: _not identified/ unremarkable<br clear="none" />9. Hilar lymph nodes: negative/ positive ( / ) not assessed (pNx)</div></div></div></div></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
