<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Urothelial carcinoma ( T ) with/ without regional lymph node</div><div>metastasis ( / N ) unassessable nodal status (NX), __</div><div>Retroperitoneal laparoscopic nephroureterectomy and bladder cuff excision</div><div><br/></div><div>REFERENCE:</div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div> 1. Kidney (_ gm and _ x _ x _ cm. with / without mild moderate severe hydronephrosis), ureter (_ cm in length, _ cm in diameter), and bladder cuff (_ x _ x _ cm)</div><div> 2. Tumor size: _ x _ x _ cm</div><div> 3. Tumor location: upper / middle/ lower pelvis.</div><div>4. Gross appearance of tumor: ulcerative, papillary</div><div>5. Adrenal gland:  not identified </div><div><br/></div><div>Representative sections are submitted and labeled as follows:</div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC DESCRIPTION:</div><div> 1. Tumor type: urothelial carcinoma, invasive (with squamous glandular differentiation)</div><div> 2. Histological grade: low-grade high-grade/or grade _/3-tier system</div><div> 3. Tumor invasion depth:</div><div> Ta (Papillary noninvasive carcinoma)</div><div> T1 (Tumor invades subepithelial connective tissue)</div><div> T2 (Tumor invades the muscularis)</div><div> T3 (For renal pelvis only) Tumor invades beyond muscularis into peripelvic fat or</div><div> the renal parenchyma T3. (For ureter only) Tumor invades beyond muscularis</div><div> into periureteric fat</div><div> T4 (Tumor invades adjacent organs, or through the kidney into the perinephric fat) </div><div><br/></div><div>4. Urothelial carcinoma in situ: not identified/present (where)</div><div> 5. Lymphovascular invasion: not identified/present</div><div> 6. Perineurial invasion: not identified/present</div><div> 7. Tumor necrosis:</div><div> 8. Renal parenchyma: free of tumor/other</div><div> *with presence of in situ extension into renal tubules or collecting ducts</div><div> *Glomerulosclerosis and interstitial infiltrate of chronic inflammatory cells are also seen.</div><div> 9. Lymph node status:</div><div>Tumor configuration: papillary</div><div> 10. Surgical margins: free/ involves the ureteral margin / bladder cuff</div><div> 11. Adrenal gland: not identified/ unremarkable</div><div>pTNM:  pT___N___ (AJCC cancer staging system, 8th edition)</div><div>TNM descriptors: not applicable; ___y(posttherapy); ___r(retreatment); ___a(autopsy);</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
