      <source-url>file:///F:\大件癌症%20form\2018%20修改版-給癌症中心\肝癌.doc</source-url>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Hepatocellular carcinoma (pT), liver, </div><div>REFERENCE:</div><div><br/></div><div style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-size: 14px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;">CLINICAL INFORMATION:</span></div><div style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-size: 14px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;">Lab data</span></div><div style="font-size: 14px;"><div><span style="font-size: 14px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;">-- Viral test: HBsAg (_IU/mL), Anti-HCV ()</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;">-- Tumor markers: AFP (_) </span></div></div><div><br/></div><div>-- CT (201_-_): </div><div>GROSS FINDINGS:</div><div>A.Liver specimen: Segment _: _ x _ x _ cm and _ gm</div><div>It had been section partially when received.</div><div>B.Tumor size: _ x _ x _ cm; capsule (present/absent); necrosis (_%)</div><div>C. Margin status: Involved / Uninvolved by invasive carcinoma; distance of invasive carcinoma from closest margin: ___ cm</div><div>D. Macroscopic Venous (Large Vessel) Invasion: present / absent</div><div>E. Non-tumorous liver: cirrhotic / non-cirrhotic</div><div>F.Other specimen(s):</div><div>- Gallbladder: _ x _ x _ cm, and wall thickness (__- _cm), with stones in the lumen. (specify other remarkable finding, when needed)</div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><br clear="none" /></div><div>Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>RA-RD: Tumor</div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;">RE: Uninvolved liver</div><div>MICROSCOPIC DESCRIPTION:</div><div>A. Histological type: Hepatocellular carcinoma/ Fibrolamellar hepatocellular carcinoma / Undifferentiated carcinoma</div><div>B. Histological grade (Edmondson and Steiner system): I / II / III / IV</div><div>C. Tumor number and size: solitary, _ x _ x _ cm / multiple ( in number), up to _ x _ x _ cm</div><div>D. Tumor Extension: Tumor confined to liver / Tumor involves a major branch of the portal vein / Tumor involves 1 or more hepatic vein(s) / Tumor involves visceral peritoneum / Tumor directly invades gallbladder / Tumor directly invades other adjacent organs ( )</div><div>E. Lymph-Vascular Invasion</div><div>- Macroscopic Venous (Large Vessel) Invasion: present / absent</div><div>_ present but not meet the  criteria of pT4 (tumor involves major branch of the portal vein or hepatic vein).</div><div>- Microscopic (Small Vessel) Invasion: present / absent</div><div>F. Margin status: Involved / Uninvolved by invasive carcinoma; distance of invasive carcinoma from closest margin: ___ cm</div><div>G. For post-TAE or TACE tumor: not applicable / _% of residual viable tumor.</div><div>H. Additional findings in the non-tumorous liver:</div><div>1. Fibrosis (Ishak score): None (0/6) / Fibrous expansion of some portal areas, with or without short fibrous septa (1/6) / Fibrous expansion of most portal areas(2/6) / Fibrous expansion of most portal areas with occasional portal-portal bridging (3/6) / Fibrous expansion of portal areas with marked bridging as well as portal-to-central bridging (4/6) / Marked bridging with occasional nodules (incomplete cirrhosis) ( 5/6) / Cirrhosis (6/6)</div><div>2. Small cell dysplasia (change): present / absent</div><div>3. Large cell dysplasia (change): present / absent</div><div>4. Steatosis (fatty change): % (macrovesicular / microvesicular / mixed)</div><div>I. Lymph node status: (沒有的話，請直接刪掉此項目)</div><div>J. Special staining studies (specify the findings when applied)</div><div><span style="color: rgb(0, 128, 128);">Masson's trichrome</span> demonstrates the fibrotic bands in non-tumorous part.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
