    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:<br clear="none" />1. Hepatocellular carcinoma (pT(  )   N___),  liver, segments    and   , hepatectomy / segmentectomy<br clear="none" />2. Negative for malignancy / Chronic cholecystitis with cholelithiasis, gallbladder, cholecystectomy<br clear="none" /><br clear="none" />PREVIOUS PATHOLOGICAL EXAM (               ):<br clear="none" /><br clear="none" /><br clear="none" />GROSS DESCRIPTION:<br clear="none" />A. Liver specimen:<br clear="none" /><br clear="none" />     1. Segment   :     x     x       cm and     gm.<br clear="none" />     2. Segment   :     x     x       cm and     gm.<br clear="none" />B. Tumor number and size:<br clear="none" />     1. Segment   : Solitary,    x     x       cm, capsule (present/absent); necrosis (   %).<br clear="none" />                            Multiple (     in number), up to    x     x       cm, capsule (present/absent); necrosis (   %).<br clear="none" />      2. Segment   : Solitary,    x     x       cm, capsule (present/absent); necrosis (   %).<br clear="none" />                             Multiple (     in number), up to    x     x       cm, capsule (present/absent); necrosis (   %).<br clear="none" />C. Margin status: <br clear="none" />    1. Segment   : Involved / Uninvolved by invasive carcinoma; distance of invasive carcinoma from closest margin: ___ cm.<br clear="none" />    2. Segment   : Involved / Uninvolved by invasive carcinoma; distance of invasive carcinoma from closest margin: ___ cm.<br clear="none" />D. Macroscopic Venous (Large Vessel) Invasion: present in segment    / absent. <br clear="none" />E. Non-tumorous liver: cirrhotic / non-cirrhotic.<br clear="none" />F. Other specimen:<br clear="none" />- Gallbladder:     x     x     cm in size and     cm in thickness; no stone / <br clear="none" />     stone(s) present, measuring (up to)    x     x     cm.<br clear="none" /><br clear="none" />Representative sections are taken and labeled as:<br clear="none" /><br clear="none" /><br clear="none" />MICROSCOPIC DESCRIPTION:<br clear="none" />A. Histological type: Hepatocellular carcinoma/ Fibrolamellar hepatocellular carcinoma / Undifferentiated carcinoma<br clear="none" />B. Histological grade (Edmondson and Steiner system): I / II / III / IV<br clear="none" />C. Tumor number and size:<br clear="none" />    1. Segment   : solitary,     x     x     cm / multiple (     in number), up to    x     x       cm. <br clear="none" />    2. Segment   : solitary,     x     x     cm / multiple (     in number), up to    x     x       cm <br clear="none" />D. Tumor Extension: <br clear="none" />    1. Segment   : Tumor confined to liver / Tumor involves a major branch of the portal vein / Tumor involves 1 or more hepatic vein(s) / Tumor involves visceral peritoneum / Tumor directly invades gallbladder / Tumor directly invades other adjacent organs (     )<br clear="none" />    2. Segment   : Tumor confined to liver / Tumor involves a major branch of the portal vein / Tumor involves 1 or more hepatic vein(s) / Tumor involves visceral peritoneum / Tumor directly invades gallbladder / Tumor directly invades other adjacent organs (     )<br clear="none" />E. Lymph-Vascular Invasion<br clear="none" />   - Macroscopic Venous (Large Vessel) Invasion: present in segment     / absent<br clear="none" />   - Microscopic (Small Vessel) Invasion: present in segment     / absent<br clear="none" />F. Margin status: <br clear="none" />    1. Segment   : Involved / Uninvolved by invasive carcinoma; distance of invasive carcinoma from closest margin: ___ cm<br clear="none" />    2. Segment   : Involved / Uninvolved by invasive carcinoma; distance of invasive carcinoma from closest margin: ___ cm<br clear="none" />G. For post-TAE or TACE tumor: <br clear="none" />    1. Segment   : not applicable /     % of residual viable tumor.<br clear="none" />    2. Segment   : not applicable /     % of residual viable tumor.<br clear="none" />H. Additional findings in the non-tumorous liver: <br clear="none" />  <br clear="none" />    1. Fibrosis (Ishak score): None (0/6) / Fibrous expansion of some portal areas, with  <br clear="none" />    or without short fibrous septa (1/6) / Fibrous expansion of most portal areas(2/6)    <br clear="none" />    / Fibrous expansion of most portal areas with occasional portal-portal bridging   <br clear="none" />    (3/6) / Fibrous expansion of portal areas with marked bridging as well as <br clear="none" />    portal-to-central bridging (4/6) / Marked bridging with occasional nodules  <br clear="none" />    (incomplete cirrhosis) ( 5/6) / Cirrhosis (6/6)<br clear="none" />    2. Small cell dysplasia (change): present/ absent<br clear="none" />    3. Large cell dysplasia (change): present/ absent<br clear="none" />   <br clear="none" />4. Steatosis (fatty change):    % (macrovesicular / microvesicular / mixed)<br clear="none" />I. Lymph node status: (沒有的話，請直接刪掉此項目)<br clear="none" /></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
