  <note>
    <title>Liver_CC</title>
    <created>20170705T080856Z</created>
    <updated>20220425T025656Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>______  (pT___N___M___); liver, (specific locations); (surgical procedure)</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>PREVIOUS PATHOLOGICAL EXAM:</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS FINDINGS:</div><div>A.Liver specimen (describe each one with specific label)</div><div>1.Segment ___: ___x __x __ cm and ___ gm</div><div>2.Segment ___: ___x __x __ cm and ___ gm</div><div>B.Tumor: __Solitary /__ Multiple (specify individually when applicable)</div><div>1.Segment ___: ___x __x __ cm; capsule (present/absent); necrosis (___%)</div><div>2.Segment ___: ___x __x __ cm; capsule (present/absent); necrosis (___%)</div><div>C.Tumor-free resection margin (in the nearest tumor): ___ cm</div><div>D.Large vessel (venous) invasion:  present / not identified</div><div>E.Non-tumorous liver: __cirrhotic (micronodular, macronodular, or mixed); __non-cirrhotic </div><div>F.Other specimen(s):</div><div>A.Gall bladder: ___ cm long, diameter (__-__ cm), and wall thickness (__-___cm), with ___ stones in the lumen. (specify other remarkable finding, when needed)</div><div>B.Other (s)</div><div><br/></div><div>Labels of the tissue sampled (prefix “A/R” implying embedded entirely /partially)</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC DESCRIPTION:</div><div>A.Histological type:</div><div> ___ Cholangiocarcinoma</div><div>___ Combined hepatocellular and cholangiocarcinoma</div><div>___ Bile duct cystadenocarcinoma</div><div>___ Other (specify): ___________________________</div><div>B.Histological grade:</div><div>__ Grade X (grade cannot be assessed)</div><div>__ Grade 1 (well differentiated, > 95% of tumor composed of glands)</div><div>__ Grade 2 (mod. Differentiated, 50–95% of tumor composed of?glands)</div><div>__ Grade 3 (poorly differentiated, 5–49% of tumor composed of glands)</div><div>__ Grade 4 (undifferentiated, &lt;5% of tumor composed of glands)</div><div>Tumor Size: </div><div>C.Tumor growth pattern:  mass-forming / periductal infiltrating / mixed</div><div>D.Tumor multicentricity:  solitary / multiple (x ___ in number)</div><div>E.Tumor invasion: (check all when applicable): </div><div>1. Confined to hepatic parenchyma:  Yes / No   </div><div>2. Carcinoma in situ (confined to intrahepatic bile ducts) :  present / not dentified</div><div>3. Invade visceral peritoneal surface:  present / not identified     </div><div>4. Invades gallbladder:  present / not identified </div><div>5. Invades adjacent organs (other than the gallbladder):  present / not identified   </div><div>6. Macroscopic invasion to large vessel(s):  present / not identified </div><div>7. Microscopic invasion to small vessel/(s):  present / not identified </div><div>8. Perineurial invasion:  present / not identified</div><div>F.Surgical margins:</div><div>Hepatic parenchymal margin: </div><div>___ Uninvolved by tumor by _____ mm wide</div><div>___ Involved by tumor</div><div>___ Cannot be assessed</div><div>Bile duct margin</div><div>___ Uninvolved by invasive carcinoma, _____ mm wide</div><div>___ Dysplasia/carcinoma in situ:  present / not identified </div><div>___ Cannot be assessed</div><div>Other Margin (specify):</div><div>___ Uninvolved by tumor by _____ mm wide</div><div>___ Involved by tumor</div><div>___ Cannot be assessed</div><div>G.Additional findings in the non-tumorous liver: (check all when applicable) </div><div>1. Type of hepatitis viral infection: B / C / not applicable</div><div>2. Biliary stones:  present / not identified   </div><div>3. Primary sclerosing cholangitis:  present / not identified </div><div>4. Activity grade of necroinflammation (of the Ishak system, 1995): ___/18</div><div>I. Periportal or periseptal interface hepatitis (piecemeal necrosis):</div><div>(0) Absent</div><div>(1) Mild (focal, few portal areas)</div><div>(2) Mild/moderate (focal, most portal areas)</div><div>(3) Moderate (continuous, around &lt;50% of tracts or septa)</div><div>(4) Severe (continuous, around >50% of tracts or septa)</div><div>II. Confluent necrosis</div><div>(0) Absent</div><div>(1) Focal confluent necrosis</div><div>(2) Zone 3 necrosis in some areas</div><div>(3) Zone 3 necrosis in most areas</div><div>(4) Zone 3 necrosis + occasional portal-central (P-C) bridging</div><div>(5) Zone 3 necrosis + multiple P-C bridging</div><div>(6) Panacinar or multiacinar necrosis</div><div>III. Focal (spotty) lytic necrosis, apoptosis and focal inflammation</div><div>(0)Absent</div><div>(1) 1 focus or less per ×10 objective</div><div>(2) 2–4 foci per ×10 objective</div><div>(3) 5–10 foci per ×10 objective</div><div>(4) More than 10 foci per ×10 objective</div><div>IV. Portal inflammation</div><div>(0) Absent</div><div>(1) Mild, some or all portal areas</div><div>(2) Moderate, some or all portal areas</div><div>(3) Moderate/marked, all portal areas</div><div>(4) Marked, all portal areas</div><div>5. Fibrotic stage (of the Ishak system, 1995): ____</div><div>(0) No fibrosis</div><div>(1) Fibrous expansion of some portal areas, with or without short fibrous septa</div><div>(2) Fibrous expansion of most portal areas, with or without short fibrous septa</div><div>(3) Fibrous expansion of most portal areas with occasional portal to portal (p-p)</div><div>bridging</div><div>(4) Fibrous expansion of portal areas with marked bridging (portal to portal</div><div>(p-p) as well as portal to central (p-c)</div><div>(5) Marked bridging (p-p and/or p-c) with occasional nodules (incomplete</div><div>cirrhosis)</div><div>(6) Cirrhosis (probable or definite)</div><div>Simple ideogram for comparison between the Ishak (1995), Metavir (1994) and</div><div>Scheuer (1991) systems is available in the reference: Duido M, et al. Dig Liver Dis (2011) 43 Suppl 4:S331-43.</div><div>H.Special staining studies (specify the findings when applied) </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Reasons for inclusion of Item-G (additional findings in the non-tumorous liver):</div><div>The HBV infection, cirrhosis, hepatolithiasis and hepatic schistosomiasis have been repeatedly demonstrated to be potential risk factors for intrahepatic cholagniocarcinoma (ICC). HBV-associated ICC shares many clinicopathological similarities with HBV-associated HCC.</div><div>References: (1) Lee CH, et al. Viral hepatitis-associated intrahepatic cholangiocarcinoma shares common disease processes with hepatocellular carcinoma. Br J Cancer. 2009; 100(11):1765-70. (2) Zhou H, et al. Hepatitis B virus-associated intrahepatic cholangiocarcinoma and hepatocellular carcinoma may hold common disease process for carcinogenesis. Eur J Cancer. 2010; 46(6):1056-61.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Liver_meta adenoCA</title>
    <created>20150723T235652Z</created>
    <updated>20251009T060007Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Liver, _, segmentectomy --- Metastatic adenocarcinoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>REFERENCE (201_-_-_):</div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div>The spceimen is a segment of liver measuring _ x _ x _ cm and _ gm. It had been sectioned partially when received. One /Multiple yellowish to whitish tumor /s is /are seen, measuring /up to _ x _ x _ cm. It is located _ cm from the nearest surgical margin.</div><div><br/></div><div>Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:</div><div>RA-RD: tumor</div><div>RE: non-tumor liver parenchyma</div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC FINDING:</div><div>Section shows hepatic parenchyma infiltrated by complex tubuloglandular structures lined by neoplastic columnar cells with (focal extravasated mucin) and necrosis. The background is desmoplastic with ductular reaction. The closest surgical margin is _ mm. The liver parenchyma shows steatosis (_%) with mild chronic inflammatory infiltrate around portal areas. No fibrosis is observed.</div><div><br/></div><div>Immunohistochemically, the tumor cells are positive for CDX-2 and CK20 but not CK7, consistent with metastatic adenocarcinoma of colorectal origin.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
