    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:<br clear="none" />1. Cirrhosis, liver, native liver; <br clear="none" />2. _, graft liver, right lobe;<br clear="none" />3. _, graft liver, left lobe;<br clear="none" />4. , recipient gallbladder; <br clear="none" />5. , donor gallbladder; <br clear="none" /> <br clear="none" />GROSS DESCRIPTION:<br clear="none" />#1. [Native liver] The specimen is a liver measuring _ x _ x _ cm and _ gm. It <br clear="none" /> had been opened when received. No focal mass lesion is seen grossly. Marked <br clear="none" /> cirrhosis is observed.<br clear="none" />#2. [Graft liver, right] One piece of tissue is seen, measuring _ x _ x _ cm.<br clear="none" />#3. [Graft liver, left] One piece of tissue is seen, measuring _ x _ x _ cm.<br clear="none" />#4. [Gallbladder, recipient] <br clear="none" /> The gallbladder measures _ x _ x _ cm with wall thickness of _ cm. <br clear="none" />#5. [Gallbladder, donor] <br clear="none" /> The gallbladder measures _ x _ x _ cm with wall thickness of _ cm.</div><p><br clear="none" /></p><div>Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:<p><br clear="none" /></p><div>MICROSCOPIC FINDING:<br clear="none" />1. Sections show liver tissue featuring distorted architecture and is replaced by hepatocyte nodules surrounded by fibrous bands containing proliferative ductules and lymphocytes. Fatty change is seen (_%).<br clear="none" />2&amp;3. Sections show micro- and macrovesicular steatosis (50%). <br clear="none" />4. The recipient gallbladder shows<br clear="none" />5. The donor gallbladder shows</div></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
