<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br clear="none" /><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">DIAGNOSIS:</span><br clear="none" /><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Adenocarcinoma () with/ lymph node metastasis (), <span></span><span><span><span>lung</span></span></span>, _</span><br clear="none" /><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">VATS _____ with lymph nodes dissection</span></div><p><br clear="none" /></p><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">PREVIOUS PATHOLOGICAL EXAM:</span><p><br clear="none" /></p><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">GROSS FINDINGS:</span><br clear="none" /><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">1. Lobectomy specimen: _ x _ x _ cm and _ gm. </span><br clear="none" /><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">2. Tumor size: _ x _ x _ cm without /with pleural retraction. </span><br clear="none" /><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">3. The tumor is located _ cm from the bronchial section margin and _ cm from the </span><br clear="none" /><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"> stapled margin. </span><br clear="none" /><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">4. _ bottles of LNs labeled as follows:</span><br clear="none" /><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"> [_ LNs] _ tissue fragments, measuring _ x _ x _ cm in total.</span><br clear="none" /><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"> [_ LNs] _ tissue fragments, measuring _ x _ x _ cm in total.</span><br clear="none" /><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"> [_ LNs] _ tissue fragments, measuring _ x _ x _ cm in total.</span><br clear="none" /><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"> [_ LNs] _ tissue fragments, measuring _ x _ x _ cm in total.</span><br clear="none" /><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"> [_ LNs] _ tissue fragments, measuring _ x _ x _ cm in total.</span><br clear="none" /><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">_ tracheobronchial LNs</span></div><div>_ pulmonary hilar LNs<br clear="none" />_ subcarinal LNs<br clear="none" />_ interloblar LNs<br clear="none" />_ tracheobronchial LNs</div><div>_ paratracheal LNs</div><div><br clear="none" /><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:</span><br clear="none" /></div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div><br clear="none" /><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">MICROSCOPIC EXAMINATION:</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">1. Histological type [ According to <span><span style="font-size: small;">classification published by the World Health Organization (WHO) for tumors of the <span></span><span><span>lung</span></span>, 2015</span></span>]:</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">___ Squamous cell carcinoma</span></span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">___ Adenocarcinoma, lepidic predominant</span></span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">___ Adenocarcinoma, acinar predominant</span></span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">___ Adenocarcinoma, papillary predominant</span></span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">___ Adenocarcinoma, solid predominant</span></span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">___ Adenocarcinoma, micropapillary predominant</span></span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">___ Minimally invasive adenocarcinoma</span></span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">___ Adenocarcinoma in situ</span></span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">___ Mucinous adenocarcinoma</span></span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">___ Fetal adenocarcinoma</span></span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">___ Enteric adenocarcinoma</span></span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span><span style="font-size: small;">[Percentage of the subtypes present: lepidic ( %), acinar ( %), papillary ( %), solid ( %), micropapillary ( %)]</span></span></span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span>2. Histological grade</span>：</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span><span style="font-size: small;">___ </span></span>well differentiated (G1).</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span><span style="font-size: small;">___ </span></span>moderately differentiated (G2).</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span><span style="font-size: small;">___ </span></span>poorly differentiated (G3).</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span><span style="font-size: small;">___ </span></span>undifferentiated (G4).</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span>3. Tumor size</span>： <span>cm</span></span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">4. Venous/ Lymphatic invasion: present / absent</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">5. Perineurial invasion: present / absent</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">6. Margin status: <br clear="none" /><span><span style="font-size: small;">___ Not applicable</span></span></span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">___ Cannot be assessed</span></span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span><span style="font-size: small;">___ Uninvolved by invasive carcinoma and carcinoma in situ <br clear="none" />[Distance of invasive carcinoma from closest margin: ___ cm]</span></span></span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">___ Involved by invasive carcinoma</span></span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">___ Involved by carcinoma in situ</span></span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">7. Visceral pleura Invasion [evaluated with elastic stain] <br clear="none" />___ Not identified (PL0)</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">___ Present, tumor extends through the elastic layer (PL1).</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">___ Present, tumor extends to the surface of the visceral pleural (PL2)</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">8. Lymph nodes status:</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span><span style="font-size: small;">___</span></span> None metastasized (0/ , N0)</span></p><p><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span><span style="font-size: small;">___ </span></span>Metastasized ( / , N ); extranodal extension: absent/present</span></p><br clear="none" /><p><br clear="none" /></p><div><br clear="none" /></div></div></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
