  <note>
    <title>Lung_pleura_empyema</title>
    <created>20150724T000151Z</created>
    <updated>20170515T055542Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>1. , _ pleura</div><div>2. Abscess, lung, _</div><div>VATS decortication and wedge resection</div><div><br/></div><div>PREVIOUS PATHOLOGICAL EXAM:</div><div>201_-_-_:</div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS FINDINGS:</div><div>#1. [Pleura, _] The specimen consists of multiple tissue fragments, measuring _ x _ x _ cm in total.</div><div>#2. [Lung, _] The specimen consists of a wedge-resected lung tissue measuring _ x _ x _ cm and _ gm, with a _ nodule/tumor measuring _ x _ x _ cm.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC EXAMINATION:</div><div>[Pleura]</div><div>The section taken from the pleura shows soft tissues with extensive necrosis, fibrin clots and infiltration of mixed inflammatory cells. No granuloma nor evidence of malignancy.</div><div>[Lung]</div><div>The lung tissue shows extensive necrosis with mixed inflammatory cells infiltration and foci of abscess formation. No evidence of granuloma or malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
