      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Modified Weiss (Weiss Revisited) System<br clear="none" />-- Mitotic rate >5/50HPF: present<br clear="none" />-- Atypical mitotic figures: absent<br clear="none" />-- Clear cells comprising &lt;25% of the tumor: present<br clear="none" />-- Necrosis: present<br clear="none" />-- Capsular invasion: present<br clear="none" />-- TOTAL POINT: <br clear="none" /></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20210608T071822Z</created>
    <updated>20210610T053055Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>myxoid adrenal cortical adenoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC FINDING:</div><div>Sections show a well-circumscribed tumor composed of lipid-</div><div>laden clear cells and small-medium size cells with</div><div>eosinophilic cytoplasm arranged in cords and pseudoglandular</div><div>pattern in a myxoid stroma. No overt atypia is seen.</div><div>Mitosis is hardly identified. Focal lymphocytic infiltrate</div><div>is noted. Immunohistochemically, the lesional cells are</div><div>positive for Melan-A but not AE1/AE3, consistent with the</div><div>diagnosis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Note. Although the tumor lacks morphologic signs of</div><div>malignancy according to criteria proposed by Weiss,</div><div>there is no final conclusion whether or not the myxoid</div><div>subtype have a distinct biologic behavior from conventional</div><div>adrenocortical adenomas, which needs to be further</div><div>elucidated. Follow-up is recommended.</div><div><br/></div><div>Reference:</div><div>Adrenocortical tumors with myxoid features: a distinct</div><div>morphologic and phenotypical variant exhibiting malignant</div><div>behavior. Am J Surg Pathol. 2010 Jul;34(7):973-83.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Neuroblastoma</title>
    <created>20170316T015417Z</created>
    <updated>20170316T015434Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Neuroblastoma,__adrenal gland, resection</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>All are embedded in five cassettes.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC DESCRIPTION:</div><div>It shows adrenal gland with one demarcated tumor composed of neuroblastic cells that</div><div>form groups or nests separated by delicate stromal septa and are positive for</div><div>synaptophysin but negative for CD99, GFAP, or S-100. Homer-Wright rosettes are noted</div><div>focally.</div><div><br/></div><div>1. Histologic Type: Neuroblastoma</div><div>2. Tumor Size: Greatest dimension: 3.0 cm</div><div>3. Degree of Differentiation: Poorly Differentiated Subtype</div><div>4. Mitotic-Karyorrhectic Index (MKI): Low (&lt;100 per 5000 cells; &lt;2%)</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>non-invasive follicular thyroid neoplasm with papillary like nuclear features. (NIFTP) see COMMENT.</title>
    <created>20211119T032104Z</created>
    <updated>20211119T032125Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>non-invasive follicular thyroid neoplasm with papillary</div><div>  like nuclear features. (NIFTP) see COMMENT.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections taken from left lobe tumor show a demarcated tumor</div><div>with capsule, composed of microfollicles</div><div>lined by follicular cells revealing nuclear enlargement,</div><div>chromatin clearing and focal presence of nuclear</div><div>pseudoinclusions. Hurthle cell change is seen.</div><div><br/></div><div>Tumor site: left lobe</div><div>Histologic type: non-invasive follicular thyroid neoplasm</div><div>  with papillary like nuclear features. (NIFTP)</div><div>Tumor Size: 1.4x1x0.9 cm</div><div>Surgical margin: Free of tumor, &lt;1 mm from margin.</div><div>Ancillary studies: CK19(positive); HBME1(negative); Ki67</div><div>  (5%); thyroglobulin(positive); synaptophysin(negative).</div><div>Additional findings:</div><div>  Right lobe: a small nodular goiter is seen.</div><div><br/></div><div>COMMENT:</div><div>The tumor is completely removed and careful examination of</div><div>the tumor capsule interface reveals no capsular or</div><div>lymphovascular invasion. The risk of recurrence or other</div><div>adverse events is extremely low (&lt;1%) within the first 15</div><div>years after resection. NIFTP can be treated with lobectomy,</div><div>allowing patients to avoid complete thyroidectomy and</div><div>radioactive iodine therapy.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Oral ajcc8</title>
    <created>20180109T080858Z</created>
    <updated>20180612T043059Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-url>file:///F:\大件癌症%20form\2018%20修改版-給癌症中心\2-Lip%20and%20oral%20cavity%20cancer.doc</source-url>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">DIAGNOSIS:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Buccal mucosa / Lip / Gum / Oral mucosa</span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">, _________, resection -----</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Tongue, _________,</span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">partial / total</span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">glossectomy -----</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Mouth angle, _________, resection -----</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Mandible,</span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">right / left</span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">side,</span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">marginal / segmental</span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">mandibulectomy -----</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Maxilla,</span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">right / left</span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">side, partial maxillectomy -----</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Lymph node,</span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">right / left</span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">neck, dissection -----</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Macroscopic examination</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;">GROSS FINDINGS:</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 11pt;">Surgical type and procedure:____, fixed in formalin</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 11pt;">Specimen integrity: Intact</span><br/></div><div><span style="font-size: 11pt;">Specimen size: </span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;"><br/></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;"><br/></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;">The specimen is received in _ separate parts as follow</span><span style="font-size: 14px;">s: </span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;">#1. [Main lesion] </span></div><div>The specimen is a fragment of tissue measuring _ x _ x _ cm and including the following structures:</div><div>-- Buccal mucosa: _ x _ cm</div><div>-- Skin: _ x _ cm</div><div>--</div><div>-- Tumor: _ x _ x _ cm</div><div>-- Margin distance:  <span style="font-size: 14px;">anterior (_ cm), posterior (_ cm), superior (_ cm), inferior (_ cm), medial (_ cm), lateral (_ cm),</span></div><div style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-size: 14px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;">and deep (_ cm) </span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.45;">#2. [] Received is a tissue fragment measuring _ x _ x _ cm including submandibular gland (_ x _ x _ cm). Stitches are labeled as level Ia, Ib, IIa, IIb and III, respectively.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;">#3. [Teeth] Received is/ are _ teeth _/tooth measuring up to _ x _ x _ cm. [Gross </span><span style="font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.45;">examination only]</span></div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;">Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;">_: LNs, level Ia</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;">_: submandibular gland</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;">_: LNs, level Ib</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;">_: LNs, level IIa</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;">_: LNs, level IIb</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;">_: LNs, level III</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic examination</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Histologic Type: (</span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">參閱附表一</span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">___ Squamous cell carcinoma, (specify variant) ____________________</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">___ Carcinoma of minor salivary glands, (specify) ____________________</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">___ Adenocarcinoma, NOS (non-salivary gland),</span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">low / intermediate / high</span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">grade</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">___ Neuroendocrine carcinoma, (specify type) ____________________</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">___ Carcinoma, type cannot be determined</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">___ Mucosal malignant melanoma</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">___ Other: (specify) ____________________________</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Histologic Grade:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">___ Not applicable,   ___ GX: Cannot be assessed,   ___ G1: Well differentiated</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">___ G2: Moderately differentiated,   ___ G3: Poorly differentiated</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">___ Other: (specify) ____________________________</span></div><div>Tumor Site: ___</div><div>Tumor Focality: single</div><div>Microscopic Tumor Extension: (specify) ____________________________<br/></div><div><ul><li><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Tumor Depth of Invasion (DOI) (millimeters):  mm</span><br/></li></ul></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Tumor Size: </span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Margins</span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">(obtained from the main resection specimen):</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">___ Cannot be assessed</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">___ Margins</span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">uninvolved / involved</span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">by invasive carcinoma</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">        Distance from closest margin: ___ mm or ___ cm</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">        (specify) ____________________________</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">___ <span>    </span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">        (specify) ____________________________</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">___ Not applicable</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Lymph-Vascular Invasion:</span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">not identified / present / indeterminate</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Perineural Invasion:</span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">not identified / present / indeterminate (intratumoral)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Neck Lymph Nodes:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">    Ipsilateral:  Number examined: ___; Number involved: ___</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">   </span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">*Contralateral (if available):  Number examined: ___; Number involved: ___</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">    Size (greatest dimension) of the largest positive lymph node: ___ cm</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">    Extranodal extension:</span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">not identified / present / indeterminate</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">附表二</span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Pathologic Staging (pTNM) (2017 AJCC 8th edition):</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">TNM Descriptors (required only if applicable) (select all that apply)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">___ m (multiple primary tumors)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">___ r (recurrent)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">___ y (post-treatment)</span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
