    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Diagnosis:</span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Buccal mucosa / Lip / Gum / Oral mucosa, _________, resection -----</span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Tongue, _________, partial / total glossectomy -----</span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Mouth angle, _________, resection -----</span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Mandible, right / left side, marginal / segmental mandibulectomy -----</span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Maxilla, right / left side, partial maxillectomy -----</span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><br/></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Macroscopic examination:</span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">The specimen is a fragment of tissue measuring _ x _ x _ cm and including the following structures:</span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">-- Buccal mucosa: _ x _ cm</span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">-- Skin: _ x _ cm</span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">--</span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">-- Tumor: _ x _ x _ cm</span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">-- Margin distance:  </span></span><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">anterior (_ cm), posterior (_ cm), superior (_ cm), inferior (_ cm), medial (_ cm), lateral (_ cm),</span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">and deep (_ cm) </span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><br/></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:</span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><br/></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Microscopic examination: </span></span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Histologic Type: Squamous cell carcinoma</span></span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Histologic Grade:</span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ Not applicable,   ___ GX: Cannot be assessed,   ___ G1: Well differentiated</span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ G2: Moderately differentiated,   ___ G3: Poorly differentiated</span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ Other: (specify) ____________________________</span></span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: Calibri;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:#ff0000;">Size of the tumor:</span></span></span> <span style="font-family: Calibri;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(1, 1, 1);">___ mm in maximum dimension</span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Microscopic Tumor Extension: </span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">    Depth of invasion: ___ mm.</span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Margins (obtained from the main resection specimen):</span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ Cannot be assessed</span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ Margins uninvolved / involved by invasive carcinoma</span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">        Distance from closest margin: ___ mm or ___ cm</span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">        (specify) ____________________________</span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ Margins uninvolved / involved by moderate and/or severe dysplasia</span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">        Distance from closest margin: ___ mm or ___ cm</span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">        (specify) ____________________________</span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">___ Not applicable</span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Lymph-Vascular Invasion: not identified / present / indeterminate</span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Perineural Invasion: not identified / present / indeterminate</span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Neck Lymph Nodes: Not applicable</span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;">pTNM:  pT___N___ (AJCC cancer staging system, 8th edition)</div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-size: 16px;">TNM descriptors: not applicable; ___y(posttherapy); ___r(retreatment);  ___a(autopsy); ___m(multiple);   </span></div><div style="text-align:start;"><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Oral SCC excision without LN</title>
    <created>20150723T091733Z</created>
    <updated>20251028T071146Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <reminder-done-time>20170111T133219Z</reminder-done-time>
      <reminder-order>1452057383999</reminder-order>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Right lower gingiva, excision --- Squamous cell carcinoma (pT).</div><div>Mandible, right, marginal resection --- Free of tumor.</div><div><br/></div><div>REFERENCE:</div><div>GROSS FINDINGS:</div><div>The specimen is a fragment of tongue /buccal mucosa (_ x _ x _ cm) with a portion of bone (_ x _ x _ cm) and tooth. An papillary an ulcerative tumor (_ x _ x _ cm) is seen on mucosa/gingiva. Four stitches are labeled as anterior (_ cm), posterior (_ cm), superior (_ cm), inferior (_ cm), medial (_ cm), lateral (_ cm),</div><div>and deep (_ cm) margins, respectively, with each margin distance in parenthesis.</div><div>Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:</div><div>R_: tumor</div><div>R_: anterior margin</div><div>R_: inferior margin</div><div>R_: posterior margin</div><div>R_: superior margin</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC FINDINGS:</div><div>Histological type: Squamous cell carcinoma</div><div>Histological grade: G1 (Well differentiated);</div><div>G2 (Moderately differentiated); G3 (Poorly differentiated)</div><div>Tumor size: _ cm in maximum dimension</div><div>Tumor invasion/extension:</div><div>  a. Depth of invasion: _ cm</div><div>  b. Organs involved (that affect staging):</div><div>Lymphovascular invasion:</div><div>Perineurial invasion:</div><div>Lymph node status: Not assessed </div><div>Surgical margins:</div><div>  a. Invasive carcinoma:</div><div>  – Free of tumor, with closest lesion-free distance for _ mm wide</div><div>  – Presence of tumor invasion</div><div>   b. Moderate and/or severe dysplasia</div><div>  Not identified, with closest lesion-free distance for _ mm wide</div><div>  Presence of moderate and/or severe dysplasia</div><div>Additional pathological finding(s):</div><div>pTNM: pT_ (AJCC cancer staging system, 8th edition)</div><div>TNM descriptors: Not applicable.</div><div><br/></div><div>(This case has been reviewed by two pathologists.)</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
