<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-size: 14px;">﻿<br clear="none" />
DIAGNOSIS: </span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;">Squamous cell carcinoma (pT) with /without lymph nodes metastasis (), _, OP<br clear="none" /><br clear="none" />
REFERENCE:</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;">GROSS FINDINGS:</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;">he specimen is received in _ separate parts as follow</span><span style="font-size: 14px;">s: </span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;">#1. [Main lesion] The specimen is a fragment of tongue /buccal mucosa (_ x _ x _ cm) with a portion of bone (_ x _ x _ cm) and tooth. An papillary an ulcerative tumor (_ x _ x _ cm) is seen on mucosa/gingiva. Four stitches are labeled as anterior (_ cm), posterior (_ cm), superior (_ cm), inferior (_ cm), medial (_ cm), lateral (_ cm),</span></div><div>and deep (_ cm) margins, respectively, with each margin distance in parenthesis.</div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div>The specimen is a fragment of tissue measuring _ x _ x _ cm and including the following structures:</div><div>-- Buccal mucosa: _ x _ cm</div><div>-- Skin: _ x _ cm</div><div>--</div><div>-- Tumor: _ x _ x _ cm</div><div>-- Margin distance:  <span style="font-size: 14px;">anterior (_ cm), posterior (_ cm), superior (_ cm), inferior (_ cm), medial (_ cm), lateral (_ cm),</span></div><div style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">and deep (_ cm) </div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;">#2. [] Received is a tissue fragment measuring _ x _ x _ cm including submandibular gland (_ x _ x _ cm). Stitches are labeled as level Ia, Ib, IIa, IIb and III, respectively.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;">#3. [Teeth] Received is/ are _ teeth _/tooth measuring up to _ x _ x _ cm. [Gross<br clear="none" />
examination only]</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;"><br clear="none" /></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;">Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;">R_: LNs, level Ia</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;">R_: submandibular gland</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;">R_: LNs, level Ib<br clear="none" /></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;">R_: LNs, level IIa<br clear="none" /></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;">R_: LNs, level IIb<br clear="none" /></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;">R_: LNs, level III<br clear="none" /></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;"><br clear="none" />
MICROSCOPIC FINDINGS:<br clear="none" />
1. Histological type:  squamous cell carcinoma <br clear="none" />
2. Histological grade:</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;">G1 (Well differentiated)<br clear="none" />
G2 (Moderately differentiated)<br clear="none" />
G3 (Poorly differentiated)<br clear="none" />
3. Tumor size: ___ (largest dimension) x ___ x ___ cm<br clear="none" />
4. Tumor invasion/extension:<br clear="none" />
a. Greatest invasion depth: ____ cm<br clear="none" />
b. Organs involved (that affect staging):<br clear="none" />
5. Venous/ Lymphatic invasion:<br clear="none" />
6. Perineurial invasion:<br clear="none" />
7. Lymph node status:<br clear="none" />
a. Ipsilateral: No. examined: ___; No. involved: ___<br clear="none" />
b. Contralateral (if available): No. examined: ___; No. involved: ___<br clear="none" />
c. Greatest dimension of the largest positive lymph node: ___ cm<br clear="none" />
d. Extra-capsular spread (ECS) : not identified / present / indeterminate<br clear="none" />
8. Surgical margins:<br clear="none" />
a. Invasive carcinoma:<br clear="none" />
– Free of tumor, with closest lesion-free distance for ___mm wide<br clear="none" />
– Presence of tumor invasion</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;">b. Moderate and/or severe dysplasia</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;">– Not identified, with closest lesion-free distance for ___mm from _ margin</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 14px;">– Presence of moderate and/or severe dysplasia<br clear="none" />
9. Additional pathological finding(s):<br clear="none" /></span><br clear="none" /></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
