  <note>
    <title>Orthotopic heart transplantation</title>
    <created>20170110T023150Z</created>
    <updated>20170110T023319Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><p><br clear="none" />DIAGNOSIS:<br clear="none" />1. Atherosclerosis, coronary artery<br clear="none" />2. Consistent with ischemic cardiomyopathy, heart<br clear="none" />Orthotopic heart transplantation</p><p><br clear="none" /></p><p>GROSS DESCRIPTION:<br clear="none" />The specimen is one opened heart measuring _x _x _ cm and _ gm. The right and left ventricles measure _ x _ x _ cm and _ x _ x _ cm, respectively. The right and left ventricular myocardium measures up to _ cm and _ cm in thickness, respectively. Interventricular septum measures up to _ cm in thickness. Areas of scarring are over the left ventricular myocardium. The right and left atria measure _ x _ x _ cm and _ x _ x _ cm, respectively. The bilateral atrial myocardium both measure up to _ cm in thickness. The left main coronary artery, left anterior descending artery (LAD), left circumflex branch (LCX), and right coronary artery are identified with atherosclerosis.  </p><p>Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:<br clear="none" />RA: LAD                                           RK: bilateral atria<br clear="none" />RB: LCX                                           RL: mitral valve   <br clear="none" />RC: RCA                                           RM: tricuspid valve <br clear="none" />RD-RG: left ventricle with fibrosis               RN: aortic valve<br clear="none" />RH: left ventricle                                RO: pulmonary valve<br clear="none" />RI: interventricular septum                       <br clear="none" />RJ: right ventricle</p><p><br clear="none" />MICROSCOPIC FINDINGS:<br clear="none" />The myocardium of the left ventricle reveal foci of interstitial fibrosis with scar formation. The valves show myxoid degeneration. The coronary arteries including LAD, LCX and RCA show severe atherosclerosing with lumen obstruction of _%, _% and _%, <br clear="none" />respectively.<br clear="none" /></p><br clear="none" /></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Ovary_cancer ajcc 8</title>
    <created>20170328T020556Z</created>
    <updated>20180403T065328Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-url>file:///F:\2018%20AJCC%20學會版本\14-Ovarian_FT_Peritoneum%20cancer%20checklist.doc</source-url>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Serous adenocarcinoma (pT__), with nodal status (N__, __/___);  right / left ovary; total hysterectomy, bilateral salpingooophorectomy, bilateral pelvic lymph node dissection, paraaortic lymph node sampling, omentectomy and appendectomy</div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS FINDINGS:</div><div>-<span style="font-size: 10pt;"> Procedure</span></div><div>- Specimen Integrity</div><div>[NOTE: For primary ovarian tumors, if the ovary containing primary tumor is removed intact into a laparoscopy bag and ruptured in the bag by the surgeon without spillage into the peritoneal cavity (to allow for removal via laparoscopy port site or small incision), the specimen integrity should be listed as “capsule intact” with a comment explaining this in the report.]</div><div>        (i) Specimen Size and Integrity of Right Ovary (if applicable)</div><div>Capsule intact/ ruptured</div><div>Fragmented</div><div>Other (specify): ____________________________</div><div>        (ii) Specimen Size and Integrity of Left Ovary (if applicable)</div><div>Capsule intact/ ruptured</div><div>Fragmented</div><div>Other (specify): ____________________________</div><div>        (iii) Specimen Size and Integrity of Right Fallopian Tube (if applicable)</div><div>Serosa intact/ ruptured</div><div>Fragmented</div><div>Other (specify): ____________________________</div><div>(iv) Specimen Size and Integrity of Left Fallopian Tube (if applicable)</div><div>Serosa intact/ ruptured</div><div>Fragmented</div><div>Other (specify): ____________________________</div><div>- Tumor Site:</div><div>(Note: Please select the primary tumor site only)</div><div>Right/ Left ovary</div><div>Bilateral ovaries</div><div>Ovary, laterality cannot be determined (explain): ___________________</div><div>Right/ Left fallopian tube</div><div>Bilateral fallopian tubes</div><div>Fallopian tube, laterality cannot be determined (explain): __________________</div><div>Right/ Left tubo-ovarian</div><div>Bilateral tubo-ovarian</div><div>Tubo-ovarian, laterality cannot be determined (explain): __________________</div><div>Primary peritoneum</div><div>- Ovarian Surface Involvement: Present (Bilateral/ Right/ Left) Absent </div><div>- Fallopian Tube Surface Involvement: Present (Bilateral/ Right/ Left) Absent</div><div>- Tumor Size</div><div>(Note: For bilateral tumors, please report maximum dimension for each primary tumor, specifying by laterality.)</div><div>Greatest dimension (centimeters): ___ cm</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>- Uterus: ___ x ___ x ___ cm and ____ gm</div><div>- <span style="font-size: 10pt;">Cervix: </span></div><div>- Endometrium: __ cm thick with no remarkable finding<br/></div><div>- Myometrium: ___ cm thick with  no remarkable finding<br/></div><div>C. Another side of ovary and Fallopian tube: free of tumor and not remarkable in size and appearance (otherwise, specify)</div><div>- Lymph nodes: described in detail below</div><div>- Omentum: __ x __ x __ cm, with no remarkable finding (otherwise, specify)</div><div>- Appendix: ___ cm long and __ cm in diameter, with nor remarkable finding </div><div><br/></div><div>Tissues sampled are labeled as followings:</div><div>O     : LN, Rt. common iliac (n= __/__)       </div><div> P     : LN, Rt. ext. iliac  (n= __/__) </div><div>Q     : LN, Rt. int. iliac (n= __/__)         </div><div>R,S  : LN, Rt. obturator  (n= __/__) </div><div>T     : LN, Rt. inguinal  (n= __/__) </div><div>U     : LN, Lt. common iliac  (n= __/__)       </div><div>V     : LN, Lt. ext. iliac  (n= __/__) </div><div>W    : LN, Lt. int. iliac  (n= __/__)         </div><div>X,Y : LN, Lt. obturator  (n= __/__) </div><div>Z     : LN, Lt. inguinal (n= __/__) </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC FINDINGS:</div><div>- Tumor histological type: </div><div>- Histologic Grade (required for serous, endometrioid, mucinous, and seromucinous carcinomas, immature teratomas, and Sertoli-Leydig cell tumors)</div><div>(Note: Serous carcinomas are graded via a 2-tier system. Immature teratomas can be graded using a 2-tier or 3-tier system. Endometrioid and mucinous carcinomas are graded via a 3-tier system. Sertoli-Leydig cell tumors are graded via a modified 3-tier grading system with grade 2 tumors being termed “intermediate differentiated.” Clear cell carcinomas, borderline epithelial neoplasms, all other malignant sex-cord stromal and germ cell tumors are not graded.)</div><div>WHO Grading System</div><div>G1: Well differentiated</div><div>G2: Moderately differentiated</div><div>G3: Poorly differentiated</div><div>GX: Cannot be assessed</div><div>Two-Tier Grading System (required for immature teratomas and serous carcinomas only)</div><div>Low grade</div><div>High grade</div><div>Other (specify): _____________________________</div><div>Not applicable</div><div>- Implants (required for advanced stage serous/seromucinous borderline tumors only)</div><div>(Note: Serous tumor implants that were formerly classified as “invasive implants” are now classified as low-grade serous carcinoma of the peritoneum.)</div><div>Not sampled</div><div>Not identified</div><div>Present (specify sites): _______________________</div><div>- Other Tissue/ Organ Involvement:</div><div>Not applicable</div><div>Not identified</div><div>Right/ Left ovary  surface involvement (+/-)</div><div>Ovary, side not specified</div><div>Right/ Left fallopian tube (in lumen or parenchyma) </div><div>Fallopian tube, side not specified</div><div>Uterus</div><div>Cervix</div><div>Pelvic peritoneum</div><div>Abdominal peritoneum</div><div>Omentum</div><div>- Largest Extrapelvic Peritoneal Focus (required only if applicable)</div><div>Microscopic</div><div>Macroscopic (2 cm or less)</div><div>Macroscopic (greater than 2 cm)</div><div>Cannot be determined (explain): _____________________</div><div>- Peritoneal/Ascitic Fluid (C-__-__-____)</div><div>Not submitted/unknown</div><div>Negative for malignancy (normal/benign)</div><div>Atypical and/or suspicious (explain): ____________________</div><div>Malignant (positive for malignancy)</div><div>Unsatisfactory/nondiagnostic (explain): ______________________</div><div>Results pending</div><div>- Regional Lymph Nodes:</div><div>       No lymph nodes submitted or found</div><div>        Positive for metastasis (/): describe locations (No. of positive nodes/ total No. of nodes)(Report if</div><div>                                                                           any metastasis > 10 mm)</div><div>        Negative for metastasis: describe locations (0/ total No. of nodes)[report if any node with</div><div>                                                                           isolated tumor cells (ITCs) no greater than 0.2 mm)</div><div> Extracapsular spread (ECS): present/absent<br/></div><div>- Additional Pathologic Findings<br/></div><div>None identified</div><div>Serous tubal intraepithelial carcinoma (STIC)</div><div>Endometriosis</div><div>Endosalpingiosis</div><div><br/></div><div>Cervix: free of tumor <br/></div><div>Endometrium: free of tumor </div><div>Myometrium: free of tumor </div><div>Appendix: free of tumor </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Ovary_endometrioma</title>
    <created>20160628T052946Z</created>
    <updated>20180130T060640Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>1. Endometrioma, right ovary</div><div>2. Endometrioma, left ovary</div><div>___</div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div>#1. [Right ovary] Multiple tissue fragments, _x _ x _  cm and _ gm in total.</div><div>#2. [Left ovary] Multiple tissue fragments, _ x _ x _ cm and _ gm in total.</div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">Grossly, the outer surface is smooth. The luminal surface is covered with old brownish clot like material.</span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;"><br/></span></div><div>Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:</div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div>MICROSCOPIC FINDING:</div><div><span style="font-size: 14px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;">Sections shows cystic lesions with variable destruction of its lining epithelium and with heavy accumulation of hemosiderin-laden macrophages in the stroma. There are occasional endometrial glandular linings and associated stroma identified. The left fallopian tube shows paratubal cysts. No malignancy is observed.</span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Ovary_serous cystadenoma</title>
    <created>20160715T031519Z</created>
    <updated>20200518T021638Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.mac</source>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>_ ovary, ___ --- Serous cystadenoma</div><div><br/></div><div>REFERENCE:</div><div>PREVIOUS PATHOLOGIC EXAMS:</div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div>Received is a cystic mass measuring _ x _ x _ cm. It had been sectioned partially, revealing a cystic lesion with smooth outer surface and containing multiple cysts filled with brownish fluid. Fibrosis and hemorrhage are seen focally.</div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div>Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:</div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;-en-paragraph:true;"><br clear="none" /></div><div>MICROSCOPIC FINDING:</div><div><span style="font-size: 14px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;">Sections show cystic spaces lined by a single layer of tall, columnar, ciliated cells with focal papillary structure. Neither stromal invasion nor overt cellular atypia is discerned.</span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Papillary microcarcinoma (1 cm or less)</title>
    <created>20190809T022219Z</created>
    <updated>20220802T020127Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><div><div style="min-height: 13pt; text-align: left;"><span style="color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt;">Papillary microcarcinoma (pT1a)</span></div><div style="min-height: 13pt; text-align: left;"><font face="Arial" style="font-size: 12pt;"><br/></font></div><div style="min-height: 18pt; text-align: left;"><span style="min-height: 18pt;"><span style="color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt;">MICROSCOPIC FINDINGS:</span></span></div><div style="min-height: 18pt; text-align: left;"><span style="min-height: 18pt;"><span style="color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt;">The thyroid gland shows features of nodular goiter and a tiny focus of atypical follicular cells with ground glass nuclei, nuclear grooves and pseudoinclusions in a fibrotic stroma.</span></span></div><ol style="margin-top: 0mm; margin-bottom: 0mm; margin-left: 0mm; padding-left: 0pt;"><li style="margin-left: 15pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 6pt; text-indent: 0pt;"><div><span style="color: rgb(255, 0, 0); font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt;">Tumor site:</span></div></li><li style="margin-left: 15pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 6pt; text-indent: 0pt;"><div><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(255, 0, 0);">Histologic type:</span> <span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(1, 1, 1);">Papillary microcarcinoma, follicular variant</span></div></li><li style="margin-left: 15pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 6pt; text-indent: 0pt;"><div><span style="color: rgb(255, 0, 0); font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt;">Histologic grade: Not applicable</span></div></li><li style="margin-left: 15pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 6pt; text-indent: 0pt;"><div><span style="color: rgb(255, 0, 0); font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt;">Tumor focality: Unifocal</span></div></li><li style="margin-left: 15pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 6pt; text-indent: 0pt;"><div><span style="color: rgb(255, 0, 0); font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt;">Tumor dimension: ______ cm, as measured microscopically</span></div></li><li style="margin-left: 15pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 6pt; text-indent: 0pt;"><div><span style="color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt;">Encapsulation: Non-encapsulation</span></div></li><li style="margin-left: 15pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 6pt; text-indent: 0pt;"><div><span style="color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt;">Capsular invasion: Not applied in this tumor</span></div></li><li style="margin-left: 15pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 6pt; text-indent: 0pt;"><div><span style="color: rgb(255, 0, 0); font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt;">Extrathyroid extension: Absent</span></div></li><li style="margin-left: 15pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 6pt; text-indent: 0pt;"><div><span style="color: rgb(255, 0, 0); font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt;">Vascular invasion: Not identified</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(255, 0, 0); font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt;">Lymphatic invasion: Not identified</span></div></li><li style="margin-left: 15pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 6pt; text-indent: 0pt;"><div><span style="color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt;">Perineural invasion: Absent</span></div></li><li><div><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-family: Arial;">Mitotic Rate: &lt;1 per 2 mm2.</span></div></li><li style="margin-left: 15pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 6pt; text-indent: 0pt;"><div><span style="color: rgb(255, 0, 0); font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt;">Margin: Free of cancer, ___ in distance</span></div></li><li style="margin-left: 15pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 6pt; text-indent: 0pt;"><div><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(255, 0, 0);">Lymph node (Positive/Total):</span> <span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(1, 1, 1);">_/_. Extranodal extension: Present / Absent</span></div></li></ol><div style="margin: 0mm 0mm 0mm 8mm; text-indent: 0mm; min-height: 18pt; text-align: left;"><span style="text-indent: 0mm; min-height: 18pt;"><span style="color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt;">Size of Largest Metastatic Deposit (centimeters): ____ cm</span></span></div><ol start="13" style="margin-top: 0mm; margin-bottom: 0mm; margin-left: 0mm; padding-left: 0pt;"><li style="margin-left: 15pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 6pt; text-indent: 0pt;"><div><span style="color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt;">Other findings: nodular goiter.</span></div></li><li style="margin-left: 15pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 6pt; text-indent: 0pt;"><div><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(255, 0, 0);">pTNM:</span> <span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(1, 1, 1);">pT1aN___ (AJCC cancer staging system, 8th edition)</span></div></li><li style="margin-left: 15pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 6pt; text-indent: 0pt;"><div><span style="color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt;">TNM descriptors: Not applicable /  m(multiple)</span></div></li><li style="margin-left: 15pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 6pt; text-indent: 0pt;"><div><span style="color: rgb(255, 0, 0); font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt;">Parathyroid gland: Absent / right/ left, upper/ lower or ectopic</span></div></li></ol><div><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(255, 0, 0); font-family: Arial;"><br/></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">(This case has been peer reviewed by two doctors.)</span></div></div><hr/><div>Papillary microcarcinomas (also historically referred to as papillary microtumor, occult, latent, or small papillary carcinoma) are not technically a specific variant but refer to papillary carcinomas that are found incidentally measuring 1 cm or less. In spite of their rather common identification in thyroid gland resections, and apparent indolent biologic behavior, it is the recommendation to issue a protocol for all cases in which papillary thyroid carcinoma is found, including subcentimeter carcinomas, whether incidentally found in a thyroid gland removed for other reasons (eg, multinodular goiter), discovered clinically (palpable, visible nodule), and/or discovered by imaging. Given the more sophisticated diagnostic (eg, imaging) modalities currently available, small (ie, less than 1 cm) lesions are being identified and resected.</div></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Parathyroid</title>
    <created>20150828T093116Z</created>
    <updated>20220113T090226Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>1. Parathyroid, right upper, parathyroidectomy ---</div><div>   Diffuse hyperplasia.</div><div>2. Parathyroid, right lower, parathyroidectomy ---</div><div>   Diffuse hyperplasia.</div><div>3. Parathyroid, left upper, parathyroidectomy ---</div><div>   Diffuse hyperplasia.</div><div>4. Parathyroid, left lower, parathyroidectomy ---</div><div>   Diffuse hyperplasia.</div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div>#1. [Parathyroid gland, right upper] _ tissue fragment_s is_are seen measuring _ x _ x _ cm_in total. ()</div><div>#2. [Parathyroid gland, right lower] _ tissue fragment_s is_are seen measuring _ x _ x _ cm_in total. ()</div><div>cm. (AB)</div><div>#3. [Parathyroid gland, left upper] _ tissue fragment_s is_are seen measuring _ x _ x _ cm_in total. ()</div><div>#4. [Parathyroid gland, left lower] _ tissue fragment_s is_are seen measuring _ x _ x _ cm_in total. ()</div><div><br/></div><div>All tissue are taken and submitted in three cassettes. (A-D)</div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC FINDING:</div><div>Sections reveal parathyroid tissue with hyperplastic change. There are secondary changes including hemorrhage with accumulation of hemosiderin-laden macrophages. No evidence of malignancy is discerned.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Phyllodes tumor</title>
    <created>20220415T052326Z</created>
    <updated>20230831T052151Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Histologic Type: </div><div>___ Phyllodes tumor, benign<br/></div><div>___ Phyllodes tumor, borderline</div><div>___ Phyllodes tumor, malignant</div><div>Tumor Size: </div><div>Stromal Cellularity: </div><div>___ Mild (stromal nuclei are non-overlapping)</div><div>___ Moderate (some overlapping stromal nuclei)</div><div>___ Marked (many overlapping stromal nuclei)</div><div>Stromal Atypia:</div><div>___ None</div><div>___ Mild (minimal variation in nuclear size, even chromatin, and smooth nuclear contours)</div><div>___ Moderate (more variation in nuclear size and irregular nuclear membranes)</div><div>___ Marked (marked nuclear pleomorphism, hyperchromasia, and irregular nuclear contours)</div><div>Stromal Overgrowth:</div><div>Stromal overgrowth is present when there is at least one low-power microscopic field (4x objective and 10x eyepiece or 22.9 mm2)</div><div>that contains stroma only without epithelial elements.</div><div>___ Absent</div><div>___ Present</div><div>___ Cannot be determined</div><div>Mitotic Rate:</div><div>Malignant phyllodes tumors have greater than or equal to 10 mitoses per 10 high-power fields (40x objective and 10x eyepiece) or</div><div>greater than or equal to 5 mitoses / mm2. <font style="color: rgb(235, 0, 115);">Benign phyllodes tumors have less than 5 mitoses per 10 HPFs</font> (less than 2.5 mitoses /</div><div>mm2).</div><div>___ None identified: _________________</div><div>___ Specify number of mitoses per 10 high power fields: _________________ mitoses per 10 High</div><div>Power Fields (HPFs)</div><div>OR</div><div>___ Specify number of mitoses per square Millimeter (mm): _________________ mitoses per mm2</div><div>___ Cannot be determined</div><div>Histologic Tumor Border: <br/></div><div>A circumscribed border is smooth and well-defined or shows a minimally irregular tumor interface with adjacent stroma. Infiltrative</div><div>(permeative) tumor borders can be focally infiltrative (unequivocal invasion into adjacent stroma in one low power field) or</div><div>extensively infiltrative (unequivocal invasion in a wide area or in multiple foci along the tumor periphery).</div><div>___ Circumscribed (well-defined; pushing)</div><div>___ Infiltrative (permeative)</div><div>+___ Focal</div><div>+___ Extensive</div><div>___ Cannot be determined</div><div>Malignant Heterologous Elements: </div><div>A phyllodes tumor is regarded as malignant when there are malignant heterologous elements, even when not all of the other</div><div>histological features of malignancy are present. This rule does not apply if the only heterologous element is well differentiated</div><div>liposarcoma. In the breast, those tumors usually lack MDM2 and CDK4 amplifications and have a low metastatic risk. A diagnosis of</div><div>malignant phyllodes tumor should therefore not be based solely on the presence of well-differentiated liposarcoma without all of the</div><div>other histologic features of malignancy.</div><div>___ Not identified</div><div>___ Liposarcoma (excluding well-differentiated liposarcoma)</div><div>___ Osteosarcoma</div><div>___ Chondrosarcoma</div><div>___ Other (specify): _________________</div><div>MARGINS: </div><div>Margin Status for Phyllodes Tumor</div><div>Margin status is listed as positive if there is ink on phyllodes tumor (i.e., the distance is 0 mm)</div><div>___ All margins negative for phyllodes tumor</div><div>Closest Margin(s) to Phyllodes Tumor (select all that apply)</div><div>___ Anterior</div><div>___ Posterior</div><div>___ Superior</div><div>___ Inferior</div><div>___ Medial</div><div>___ Lateral</div><div>+Distance from Phyllodes Tumor to Closest Margin<br/></div><div>Specify in Millimeters (mm)</div><div>___ Exact distance: _________________ mm</div><div>___ Less than: _________________ mm</div><div>___ Greater than: _________________ mm</div><div>___ Other (specify): _________________</div><div>___ Cannot be determined (explain): _________________</div><div>___ Phyllodes tumor present at margin</div><div>Margin(s) Involved by Phyllodes Tumor (select all that apply)</div><div>___ Anterior</div><div>___ Posterior</div><div>___ Superior</div><div>___ Inferior<br/></div><div>___ Medial</div><div>___ Lateral</div><div>___ Other (specify): _________________</div><div>___ Cannot be determined (explain): _________________</div><div>Regional Lymph Node Status: </div><div>___ Not applicable (no regional lymph nodes submitted or found)</div><div>___ Regional lymph nodes present</div><div>___ All regional lymph nodes negative for tumor</div><div>___ Tumor present in regional lymph nodes</div><div>Number of Lymph Nodes with Tumor</div><div>___ Exact number (specify): _________________</div><div>___ At least (specify): _________________</div><div>___ Other (specify): _________________</div><div>___ Cannot be determined (explain): _________________</div><div>___ Other (specify): _________________</div><div>___ Cannot be determined (explain): _________________</div><div>Number of Lymph Nodes Examined</div><div>___ Exact number (specify): _________________</div><div>___ At least (specify): _________________</div><div>___ Other (specify): _________________</div><div>___ Cannot be determined (explain): _________________</div><div>+Regional Lymph Node Comment: _________________</div><div><br/></div><div>PATHOLOGIC STAGE CLASSIFICATION (pTNM, AJCC 8th Edition) </div><div>Staging applies only to malignant phyllodes tumors. pT and pN categories should not be assigned for benign and borderline tumors.</div><div>Pathologic Stage Classification (pTNM, AJCC 8th Edition) (required only if the tumor is malignant)</div><div>Reporting of pT, pN, and (when applicable) pM categories is based on information available to the pathologist at the time the report</div><div>is issued. As per the AJCC (Chapter 1, 8th Ed.) it is the managing physician’s responsibility to establish the final pathologic stage</div><div>based upon all pertinent information, including but potentially not limited to this pathology report.</div><div>___ Not applicable (tumor is not graded as malignant)</div><div><br/></div><div>___ Tumor is malignant</div><div>TNM Descriptors (select all that apply)</div><div>___ Not applicable</div><div>___ m (multiple)</div><div>___ r (recurrent)</div><div>___ y (post treatment)</div><div>pT Category</div><div>___ pT not assigned (cannot be determined based on available pathological information)</div><div>___ pT0: No evidence of primary tumor</div><div>___ pT1: Tumor 5 cm or less in greatest dimension</div><div>___ pT2: Tumor more than 5 cm but not more than 10 cm</div><div>___ pT3: Tumor more than 10 cm but not more than 15 cm</div><div>___ pT4: Tumor more than 15 cm in greatest dimension</div><div>pN Category</div><div>When no lymph nodes are present, the pathologic 'N' category is not assigned (pNX is not used and should not be reported)</div><div>___ pN not assigned (no nodes submitted or found)</div><div>___ pN not assigned (cannot be determined based on available pathological information)</div><div>___ pN0: No regional lymph node metastasis or unknown lymph node status</div><div>___ pN1: Regional lymph node metastasis</div><div>pM Category (required only if confirmed pathologically)</div><div>___ Not applicable - pM cannot be determined from the submitted specimen(s)</div><div>___ pM1: Distant metastasis</div><div>ADDITIONAL FINDINGS</div><div>+Additional Findings (select all that apply)</div><div>___ Fibroepithelial proliferation (coexisting fibroadenoma or fibroadenomatoid change in the tissue</div><div>surrounding the phyllodes tumor)</div><div>___ Atypical ductal hyperplasia</div><div>___ Atypical lobular hyperplasia</div><div>___ Other (specify): _______________</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Prostate Biopsy (x4)</title>
    <created>20151203T062318Z</created>
    <updated>20260203T031013Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS: </div><div>Adenocarcinoma (with Gleason sum, ___)</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC DESCRIPTION:</div><div>A. Tumor histological type: adenocarcinoma</div><div>B. Tumor histological grade:</div><div>R't anterior: primary score (__) + secondary score (__) = ___</div><div>R't posterior primary score (__) + secondary score (__) = ___</div><div>L't anterior: primary score (__) + secondary score (__) = ___</div><div>L't posterior primary score (__) + secondary score (__) = ___</div><div>_ Grade group 1 (Gleason Score 3 + 3 = 6) </div><div>_ Grade group 2 (Gleason Score 3 + 4 = 7) </div><div>_ Grade group 3 (Gleason Score 4 + 3 = 7) </div><div>_ Grade group 4 (Gleason Score 4 + 4 = 8) </div><div>_ Grade group 4 (Gleason Score 3 + 5 = 8) </div><div>_ Grade group 4 (Gleason Score 5 + 3 = 8) </div><div>_ Grade group 5 (Gleason Score 4 + 5 = 9) </div><div>_ Grade group 5 (Gleason Score 5 + 4 = 9) </div><div>_ Grade group 5 (Gleason Score 5 + 5 = 10)</div><div>C. Tumor volume:</div><div>__ R't anterior: tumor detected in __ of the ___ tissue cores, involving __ % of these tissue cores</div><div>__ R't posterior: tumor detected in __ of the ___ tissue cores, involving __ % of these tissue cores</div><div>__ L't anterior: tumor detected in __ of the ___ tissue cores, involving __ % of these tissue cores</div><div>__ L't posterior: tumor detected in __ of the ___ tissue cores, involving __ % of these tissue cores</div><div>D. Lymphovascular invasion: absent</div><div><br/></div><div>E. Immunohistochemical studies: No basal cells surrounding the neoplastic glands are demonstrated by p63 and 34βE12. The neoplastic glands are positive for p504s, confirming the diagnosis.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Prostate_radical</title>
    <created>20150724T000053Z</created>
    <updated>20241104T022421Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Adenocarcinoma (pT__), with nodal status (N__, __/__), prostate</div><div>Robotic-assisted laparoscopic extraperitoneal radical prostatectomy and bilateral pelvic LN dissection</div><div>術式:__</div><div>REFERENCE:</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div>The specimens are in _ containers:</div><div>#1. [Prostate]: _ x _ x _ cm and _ gm. Right vas deferens measures _ x _ cm and left vas deferens measures _ x _ cm (length x diameter). Right seminal vesicle measures _ x _ x _ cm and left seminal vesicle measures _ x _ x _ cm. Ink labeling: anterior (green); posterior (black).</div><div>#2. [Preprostate fat] _ piece_s of tissue, _ x _ x _ cm _in total.</div><div>#3. [Right pelvic LN] _ piece_s of tissue, _ x _ x _ cm _in total.</div><div>#4. [Left pelvic LN] _ piece_s of tissue, _ x _ x _ cm _in total.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:</div><div>AA: p<span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">reprostate fat</span></span></div><div>RB-RC: right vas deferens and seminal vesicle</div><div>RD-RE: left vas deferens and seminal vesicle</div><div>RF: right apex</div><div>RG: left apex</div><div>RH-RS: right lobe (mapping: )</div><div>RT-Rc: left lobe (mapping: )</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC DESCRIPTION:</div><div>A. Tumor histological type: adenocarcinoma</div><div>B. Tumor histological grade: __ differentiation</div><div>    Primary score (__) + secondary score (__) = ___</div><div>Reference:</div><div>1.Well differentiation (Gleason sun, 6 or less); moderate (7); poor (8-10)</div><div>2.Simple definitions for Gleason grade:</div><div>Grade 1: Well-circumscribed nodule of adenocarcinoma composed of crowded well-differentiated glands;</div><div>Grade 2: Similar to pattern 1 but with minor infiltration at border;</div><div>Grade 3: Well-formed glands infiltrating benign glands;</div><div>Grade 4: Fused poorly-defined glands, large cribriform glands, hypernephroid pattern;</div><div>Grade 5: Undifferentiated masses or single cells</div><div>C. Tumor volume:</div><div>__ Less than 5% (pT1a)</div><div>__ More than 5% (approximately ___%) (Right lobe: ___%; Left lobe: ___%)</div><div>D. Lymphovascular invasion: present / absent </div><div>Perineural invasion</div><div>E. Extraprostatic Extension (check all that apply):</div><div>__ Present: Specify site(s): ________</div><div>__ Absent</div><div>___Indeterminate due to intraprostatic or capsular incision  (pT2+)</div><div>F. Seminal Vesicle Invasion (check all that apply): present / absent</div><div>G. Margins:</div><div>__ Not involved by invasive carcinoma</div><div>__ Involved by invasive carcinoma: Specify site(s):  </div><div>Positive margin (incisional or in an area of EPE)</div><div><br/></div><div>H. Lymph node status: no metastasis (/)</div><div>__ Metastasis: detected in __ of the ___ LNs found</div><div>__ Extracapsular spread (ECS): present / absent</div><div>I. Other findings: </div><div>1. The preprostate fat is …..</div><div>2. Intraductal Carcinoma (IDC): present absent</div><div>J. Tumor staging (for Prostatectomy)</div><div>__ pT2: Organ confined</div><div>__ pT3: Extraprostatic extension</div><div>__ pT3a: Extraprostatic extension</div><div>__ pT3b: Seminal vesicle invasion</div><div>__ pT4: Gross invasion of bladder and/or rectum</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Salivary gland_ Pleomorphic adenoma (mixed tumor)</title>
    <created>20160628T053426Z</created>
    <updated>20260320T054338Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>_____ gland, OP --- Pleomorphic adenoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>REFERENCE:</div><div>PREVIOUS PATHOLOGIC EXAMS:</div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div>Received is a tissue fragment measuring _ x _ x _ cm and _ gm, including salivary gland and one well-demarcated tumor measuring _ x _ x _ cm.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:</div><div><br/></div><div>Pleomorphic adenoma.</div><div>MICROSCOPIC FINDING:</div><div>Section shows a well-circumscribed tumor with adjacent salivary gland tissue. The tumor is composed of bland-looking mononuclear cells arranged in sheets and occasionally tubules, in fibromyxoid, hyalinized stroma. Squamoid differentiation is focally seen. _ lymph node /s is identified with preserved nodal architecture. No malignancy is observed.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
