  <note>
    <title>Small bowel, ischemic necrosis with perforation</title>
    <created>20161130T111917Z</created>
    <updated>20250108T024702Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Ischemic necrosis with perforation, _, __</div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div>Received is a segment of intestine measuring _ cm in length and _ cm in</div><div>  diameter. The intestine is gangrenous which shows dark-red in color, involving</div><div>  about _ cm long of the segment. A _cm perforation is seen, located _ cm from</div><div>  one surgical margin. _ cm from one surgical margin is free of ischemic change</div><div>  grossly.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:</div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC FINDING:</div><div>Sections taken from _ show mucosal necrosis and hemorrhage within the</div><div>bowel wall. Sections taken from sites of perforation show destruction of whole bowel</div><div>wall with suppurative inflammation.</div><div><br/></div><div>The surgical margins show gangrenous change.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>There is no evidence of malignancy.</div><div>    </div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
