  <note>
    <title>Teratoma (with brain)</title>
    <created>20170305T110345Z</created>
    <updated>20190130T072306Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.mac</source>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-size: 14px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;">mature cystic teratoma.</span></div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The ovarian tumor is lined by bland-looking squamous epithelium with keratinous materials production, accompanied by skin appendages, fat, smooth muscles and cartilage in the underlying stroma. Associated foreign body reactions are present. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Section _ contains areas of differentiated neoroepithelial component, in which cerebral cortex development is seen in places. </div><div><br/></div><div>No immature component is observed.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Teratoma, immature</title>
    <created>20170305T110449Z</created>
    <updated>20190130T072227Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.mac</source>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: gotham;"><br/></span></div><div>Sections show an immature teratoma, grade _. The immature component is composed of imm immature neuroepiethelium and mesenchymal tissue. The immature neuroepithelial tissue occupies _ LPFs/slide. Mature components, such as squamous epithelium, skin appendages, intestinal epithelium, bone, cartilage, and mesenchymal tissue are also present.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
