<div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;"><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Hemorrhagic necrosis, consistent with testicular torsion, testis, _, _orchiectomy</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div>The specimen consists of a testis (_ x _ x _ cm and _ gm) and epididymis (_ x _ x _ cm) with torsion of spermatic cord. On cut sections, the testis and epididymis show hemorrhage and necrosis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:</div><div>: testis and epididymis</div><div>: spermatic cord</div><div><br/></div><div> </div><div>MICROSCOPIC FINDING:</div><div>Sections show extensive hemorrhagic necrosis of testis epididymis, consistent with </div><div>torsion. There is no evidence of malignancy.</div></div></div><div><br/>

</div></en-note>      ]]>
