    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><p><br clear="none" /></p><div><br clear="none" />
術式: __<br clear="none" />
REFERENCE:
<p><br clear="none" /></p></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:<br clear="none" />
The specimens are in _ labeled containers.<br clear="none" />
#1.[_Right/Left thyroid] The specimen is a lobe of thyroid, measuring _ x _ x _ cm and _ gm, including a nodule, measuring _ x _ x _ cm. On cut sections, it reveals jelly-like appearance with _hemorrhage and _calcification and _cystic change.<br clear="none" />
#2.[_Right Left thyroid] The specimen is a fragment of thyroid, measuring _ x _ x _ cm and _ gm, without gross tumor.
<p><br clear="none" /></p></div><div>Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:<br clear="none" />
R : nodule of right/ left thyroid<br clear="none" />
R : right/ left thyroid<br clear="none" />
R : regional lymph nodes<br clear="none" />
R :</div><div><br/></div><div>The entire specimen is taken and submitted in _ cassettes. </div><div>MICROSCOPIC FINDINGS:<br clear="none" />
The thyroid gland exhibits variably dilated follicular glands that are lined by flattened, inactive epithelium and filled with abundant colloid material. No evidence of malignancy is observed.
<p><br clear="none" /></p><div>*There is associated secondary changes including hemorrhage, calcification and cystic degeneration.
<p><br clear="none" /></p><div><br clear="none" /></div></div></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
