    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; line-height: 1.45;">Diagnosis:</span><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">1. Thyroid gland, right/ left lobe/ isthmus, total/subtotal thyroidectomy or lobectomy</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">---</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">2. Thyroid gland, right/ left lobe/ isthmus, total/subtotal thyroidectomy or lobectomy</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">---</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">3. Lymph nodes, level VI, neck, biopsy/dissection</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">---</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">4. Lymph nodes, level II, III, IV, right/ left neck, biopsy/dissection</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">---</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">*5. Parathyroid, location, total/subtotal thyroidectomy or lobectomy or biopsy ---</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"> </span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Macroscopic Examination:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">1. Specimen received:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Right lobe: </span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">weight: _ </span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">gm; size:</span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"> _</span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">x</span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">_</span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">x_</span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"> </span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">cm</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Left lobe: <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">weight: _ </span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">gm; size:</span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"> _</span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">x</span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">_</span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">x_</span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"> </span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">cm</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">2. Tumor description:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Number:</span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"> _</span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">; size:</span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"> _</span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">x_</span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">x_</span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">cm; </span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Location: right/ left lobe/ isthmus</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Encapsulation: yes/ no, complete/ incomplete</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Nearest distance to surgical margin:</span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">   </span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">cm</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">3. Secondary changes: fibrosis/ hemorrhage/ cystic degeneration/ calcification/ others, specify:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">4. Non-neoplastic thyroid gland: unremarkable/ nodular hyperplasia/ others, specify:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">5. Lymph node dissection (level _): _x_x_ cm </span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;"> </span><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic Examination</span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">:</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: 新細明體; color: red; mso-font-kerning: 1.0pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-TW; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">Tumor site</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">1. Tumor types:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">  </span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Papillary carcinoma,</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">classic variant</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">encapsulated follicular variant, with capsular/vascular invasion</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">encapsulated follicular variant, noninvasive</span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">*(a subset of noninvasive tumors can now be reclassified as NIFTP)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">infiltrative follicular variant</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">tall cell/ cribriform-morular/ diffuse sclerosing/ other variants, specify: ___</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">  </span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">*Noninvasive follicular thyroid neoplasm with papillary like nuclear features (NIFTP)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">  </span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Follicular carcinoma, encapsulated angioinvasive/ minimally/ widely invasive</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">  </span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Oncocytic (Hürthle) cell carcinoma, encapsulated angioinvasive/ minimally/ widely invasive</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">  </span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Poorly differentiated carcinoma</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">  </span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Undifferentiated (anaplastic) carcinoma, focal or minor component without extrathyroidal extension/ major component</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">  </span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Medullary carcinoma</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">2. Tumor size:</span> <span style="line-height: 1.45;"> _</span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">x_</span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">x</span><span style="line-height: 1.45;"> _ </span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">cm; </span><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">3. Encapsulation: absent/ partial/ complete</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">4. Capsular invasion: not identified/ minimal/ extensive/ indeterminate</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">5. Vascular invasion: not identified/ present/ indeterminate</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">*focal (less than 4 vessels)/ extensive (4 or more vessels)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">6. Lymphatic invasion: not identified/ present/ indeterminate</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">*7. Perineural invasion: not identified/ present/ indeterminate</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">8. Extrathyroid extension: not identified/ present/ indeterminate</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">microscopic adipose tissue extension</span> <span style="line-height: 1.45;">*(not upstaging)</span><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">invading only strap muscles (pT3b)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">invading subcutaneous soft tissues/ larynx/ trachea/ esophagus/ recurrent laryngeal nerve (pT4a)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">invading prevertebral fascia or encasing the carotid artery/ mediastinal vessels (pT4b)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">9. Surgical margin: cannot be accessed/ involved/ uninvolved</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">10. Additional pathologic finding(s): adenoma/ adenomatoid nodules or nodular hyperplasia/ diffuse hyperplasia (Graves disease)/ thyroiditis, specify:</span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">   </span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">/ C-cell hyperplasia/ others, specify:____</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">*11. Parathyroid gland: absent/ present; number: ____, unremarkable/ hyperplasia/</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">  </span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">others, specify: ____</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">12. Lymph nodes:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">No lymph nodes submitted or found</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Level VI: ___/___ (positive/ total)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Level VII: ___/___ (positive/ total)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">  </span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Level II, III, VI: ___/___ (positive/ total)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">  </span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Others (specify) _____: ___/___ (positive/ total)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">  </span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">*Extranodal extension: not identified/ present/ indeterminate</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">13. Comments:</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">NOTE: For All Carcinomas of the Thyroid</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Primary Tumor (pT)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pTX: Cannot be assessed</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pT0: No evidence of primary tumor</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pT1: Tumor ≤2 in greatest dimension, limited to the thyroid</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pT1a: Tumor ≤1 cm in greatest dimension limited to the thyroid</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pT1b: Tumor >1 cm but ≤2 cm in greatest dimension, limited to the thyroid</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pT2: Tumor >2 cm, but ≤4 cm in greatest dimension, limited to thyroid</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pT3: Tumor >4 cm limited to the thyroid, or gross extrathyroidal extension invading only strap muscles</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pT3a: Tumor >4 cm limited to the thyroid</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pT3b: Gross extrathyroidal extension invading only strap muscles (sternohyoid, sternothyroid, thyrohyoid, or omohyoid muscles) from a tumor of any size</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pT4: Gross extrathyroidal extension beyond the strap muscles</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pT4a: Gross extrathyroidal extension invading subcutaneous soft tissues, larynx, trachea, esophagus, or recurrent laryngeal nerve from a tumor of any size</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pT4b: Gross extrathyroidal extension invading prevertebral fascia or encasing the carotid artery or mediastinal vessels from a tumor of any size</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"> </span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Regional Lymph Nodes (pN)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pNX: Regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pN0: No regional lymph node metastasis</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pN0a: One or more cytologically or histologically confirmed benign lymph nodes</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">N0b: Defined as no radiologic or clinical evidence of locoregional lymph node metastasis.</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pN1: Metastasis to regional nodes</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pN1a: Metastasis to level VI or VII (pretracheal, paratracheal, or prelaryngeal/Delphian, or upper mediastinal) lymph nodes. This can be unilateral or bilateral disease.</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">pN1b: Metastasis to unilateral, bilateral, or contralateral lateral neck lymph nodes (levels I, II, III, IV, or V) or retropharyngeal lymph nodes</span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Thyroid_CA</title>
    <created>20150723T235949Z</created>
    <updated>20170111T034343Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS: *(Incorporated with the frozen section diagnosis)<br clear="none" />1. Papillary carcinoma (T ) with/ without regional lymph nodes metastasis <br clear="none" /> ( / N ), right / left thyroid<br clear="none" />2., right/ left thyroid<br clear="none" />Endothyroidectomy</div><p><br clear="none" /></p><div>術式: __<br clear="none" />REFERENCE:<p><br clear="none" /></p></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:<br clear="none" />The specimens are in _ labeled containers.<br clear="none" />#1.[_Right/Left thyroid] The specimen is a lobe of thyroid, measuring _ x _ x _ cm and _ gm, including a well-circumscribed, firm tumor measuring _ x _ x _ cm, _with/without satellite nodule.<br clear="none" />#2.[_Right Left thyroid] The specimen is a lobe of thyroid, measuring _ x _ x _ cm and _ gm, without gross tumor.<br clear="none" />#3. [Right lymph nodes] There are fragments of soft tissue measuring _ x _ x _ cm in total.<p><br clear="none" /></p></div><div><br clear="none" />Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:<br clear="none" />R : tumor of right/ left thyroid<br clear="none" />R : right/ left thyroid<br clear="none" />R : regional lymph nodes<br clear="none" />R :<p><br clear="none" /></p></div><div>MICROSCOPIC FINDINGS:<br clear="none" />No papillary tumor is left in the sections. The frozen section (_) is reviewed, and it shows a small focus of papillary carcinoma. The following histologic details are defined with incorporation of the findings of the frozen section.<p><br clear="none" /></p></div><div><p><br clear="none" /></p></div><div>1. Tumor types: <br clear="none" /> a. Papillary carcinoma/ classical/ follicular/ macrofollicular/ encapsulated/ microcarcinoma/ *solid/ *oncocytic/ *tall cell/ *clear cell/ *cribriform-morular/ *diffuse sclerosing/ *warthin-like/ others, specify: _______<br clear="none" /> b. Follicular/oncocytic (Hurthle) cell carcinoma, minimally/ widely invasive <br clear="none" /> c. Poorly differentiated carcinoma (including insular carcinoma)<br clear="none" /> d. Undifferentiated (anaplastic) carcinoma<br clear="none" /> e. Medullary carcinoma<br clear="none" /> f. Others, specify: _____<br clear="none" />2. Tumor size: x cm, (if more than one) x cm to x cm<br clear="none" />3. Encapsulation: absent/ partial/ complete<br clear="none" />4. Capsular invasion: absent/ minimal/ extensive<br clear="none" />5. Lymph-vascular invasion: absent/ present, focal (less than 4 vessels) or </div><div> extensive (4 or more vessels)/ indeterminate</div><div><span style="font-family:gotham, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;">Psammoma bodies only</span>

</div><div>6. Extrathyroid extension: absent/ minimal (to perithyroid soft tissue or <br clear="none" /> skeletal muscle)/ extensive (to adjacent organs or subcutaneous tissue)<br clear="none" />7. Surgical margin involvement: absent/ present, nearest distance to tumor: <br clear="none" /> ____ mm/ indeterminate<br clear="none" />8. Multicentricity: absent/ present, multiple microscopic foci (in addition to the main tumor)</div><div>in the right lobe<br clear="none" />9. Other pathologic finding(s): nodular goiter/diffuse hyperplasia (Graves disease)/ lymphocytic thyroiditis/ adenoma/ atrophy/ fibrosis/ psammoma body/ C-cell hyperplasia/ others, specify:____<br clear="none" />10. Parathyroid gland: absent/ present; number: ____, normal/ hyperplasia/ <br clear="none" /> others, specify: ____<br clear="none" />11. Lymph nodes: <br clear="none" /> - Level VI: ___/___ (positive/ total); largest metastatic size: _____ mm<br clear="none" /> - Level II, III, VI: ___/___ (positive/ total)</div><div> - Others (specify) _____ : ___/___ (positive/ total)</div><div>Psammoma bodies are seen within lymph nodes.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Thyroid_Graves disease</title>
    <created>20160624T014524Z</created>
    <updated>20160624T014707Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br clear="none" />DIAGNOSIS:<br clear="none" />1. Consistent with Graves disease,  thyroid, right lobe<br clear="none" />2. Consistent with Graves disease, thyroid, left lobe<br clear="none" />___OP<br clear="none" /><br clear="none" />CLINICAL INFORMATION:<br clear="none" />-- Anti-Tg _ IU/mL (_), Anti-TPO _ IU/mL (_), TSH _ uIU/mL (_), T3 _ ng/dl, T4 _ ug/dl<br clear="none" /><br clear="none" /><br clear="none" />GROSS DESCRIPTION:<br clear="none" />#1. [Right thyroid] Received is a lobe of thyroid measuring _ x _ x _ cm and _ gm. The thyroid is diffusely enlarged.<br clear="none" /><br clear="none" />#2. [Left thyroid]<span> Received is a lobe of thyroid measuring </span><span>_ x _ x _</span><span> cm and _ gm. The thyroid is diffusely </span><span>enlarged.</span><br clear="none" /><br clear="none" /><br clear="none" />Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:<br clear="none" /><br clear="none" /><br clear="none" />MICROSCOPIC DESCRIPTIONS:<br clear="none" />1&amp;2. Sections show hyperplastic follicles with papillary infolding, lined by cuboidal epithelium with uniform nuclei and prominent scalloping of the colloid. The stroma contains aggregates of lymphoid tissue with focal germinal center formation. The clinical and pathologic features are consistent with Graves disease. One lymph node is identified over right specimen with preserved nodal architecture. No malignancy is observed.<br clear="none" /><br clear="none" /><br clear="none" /></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Thyroid_papillary CA (incidental findings)</title>
    <created>20150723T235910Z</created>
    <updated>20250418T003903Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <reminder-done-time>20170111T133158Z</reminder-done-time>
      <reminder-order>1471417011000</reminder-order>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Papillary carcinoma (T ) with/ without regional lymph nodes metastasis ( / N ), right / left thyroid</div><div><br/></div><div>術式: __</div><div>REFERENCE:</div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div>The specimens are in _ labeled containers.</div><div>#1.[_Right/Left thyroid] The specimen is a lobe of thyroid, measuring _ x _ x _ cm and _ gm, including a nodule, measuring _ x _ x _ cm. On cut sections, it reveals jelly-like appearance with _hemorrhage and _calcification and _cystic change.</div><div>#2.[_Right Left thyroid] The specimen is a fragment of thyroid, measuring _ x _ x _ cm and _ gm. No tumor mass is identified by gross examination. </div><div><br/></div><div>Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:</div><div>R : nodule of right/ left thyroid</div><div>R : right/ left thyroid</div><div>R : regional lymph nodes</div><div>R :</div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC FINDINGS:</div><div>The thyroid gland shows features of nodular goiter and a tiny focus of atypical follicular cells with ground glass nuclei, nuclear grooves and pseudoinclusions in a fibrotic stroma. These atypical follicular cells are immunoreactive to CK19 and HBME-1, but not CD56, consistent with neoplastic nature.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>1. Tumor types: </div><div> a. Papillary carcinoma/ classical/ follicular/ macrofollicular/ encapsulated/ microcarcinoma/ *solid/ *oncocytic/ *tall cell/ *clear cell/ *cribriform-morular/ *diffuse sclerosing/ *warthin-like/ others, specify: _______</div><div> b. Follicular/oncocytic (Hurthle) cell carcinoma, minimally/ widely invasive </div><div> c. Poorly differentiated carcinoma (including insular carcinoma)</div><div> d. Undifferentiated (anaplastic) carcinoma</div><div> e. Medullary carcinoma</div><div> f. Others, specify: _____</div><div>2. Tumor size: x cm, (if more than one) x cm to x cm</div><div>3. Encapsulation: absent/ partial/ complete</div><div>4. Capsular invasion: absent/ minimal/ extensive</div><div>5. Lymph-vascular invasion: absent/ present, focal (less than 4 vessels) or </div><div> extensive (4 or more vessels)/ indeterminate</div><div>6. Extrathyroid extension: absent/ minimal (to perithyroid soft tissue or </div><div> skeletal muscle)/ extensive (to adjacent organs or subcutaneous tissue)</div><div>7. Surgical margin involvement: absent/ present, nearest distance to tumor: </div><div> ____ mm/ indeterminate</div><div>8. Multicentricity: absent/ present</div><div>9. Other pathologic finding(s): nodular goiter/diffuse hyperplasia (Graves disease)/ lymphocytic thyroiditis/ adenoma/ atrophy/ fibrosis/ psammoma body/ C-cell hyperplasia/ others, specify:____</div><div>10. Parathyroid gland: absent/ present; number: ____, normal/ hyperplasia/ </div><div> others, specify: ____</div><div>11. Lymph nodes: </div><div> - Level VI: ___/___ (positive/ total); largest metastatic size: _____ mm</div><div> - Level II, III, VI: ___/___ (positive/ total)</div><div> - Others (specify) _____ : ___/___ (positive/ total)</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Thyroid_subacute granulomatous thyroiditis</title>
    <created>20170117T011857Z</created>
    <updated>20170117T012007Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Subacute granulomatous thyroiditis (de Quervain thyroiditis), thyroid, bilateral lobes, ___</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div>#1. [Thyroid, right lobe] measuring _ x _ x _ cm and _ gm. It is vaguely nodular and firm in consistency. </div><div><br/></div><div>#2. [Thyroid, left lobe,] measuring _ x _ x _ cm and _ gm. It is  vaguely nodular and firm in consistency. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>The entire specimen is taken and submitted in _ cassettes.  </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC FINDING:</div><div>Sections show focally destroyed thyroid follicles by marked inflammatory infiltrate which is composed of lymphocytes, plasma cells, neutrophils, and epithelioid histiocytes. Granulomas containing multinucleated giant cells are seen both within the</div><div>thyroid follicles and interfollicular regions. There is also interfollicular fibrosis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Immunohistochemically, IgG highlights scattered plasma cells without increased IgG4/IgG ratio as determined by immunostains, excluding IgG4 related disease. There are no mycobacterial microorganisms as demonstrated by acid fast, and </div><div>Auramine-Rhodamine stains. No fungus is demonstrated by GMS and PAS. </div><div><br/></div><div>Taken together, the overall features are compatible with subacute granulomatous thyroiditis (de Quervain thyroiditis). _ lymph nodes are identified with preserved nodal architecture. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Urinary bladder_UC_cystectomy</title>
    <created>20150723T235852Z</created>
    <updated>20151113T034837Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:<br clear="none" />Urothelial carcinoma (T ) with without regional lymph nodes metastasis ( / , N ), urinary <span>bladder</span>, partial radical cystectomy</div><p><br clear="none" /></p><div>REFERENCE:<p><br clear="none" /></p><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:<br clear="none" />1. <span>Bladder</span> size: _ x _ x _ cm. <br clear="none" /> Length of right ureter: _ cm. Left ureter: _ cm.<br clear="none" />2. Tumor<br clear="none" />a. Characteristics: ulcerated; unifocal multifocal lesions<br clear="none" />b. Size: _ x _ x _ cm<br clear="none" />c. Location: in trigone anterior wall posterior wall dome; papillary <br clear="none" />3. Other specimens:<br clear="none" /> Prostate size: _ x _ x _ cm.<br clear="none" /> Seminal vesicles. Right: _ x _ x _ cm; Left: _ x _ x _ cm.<br clear="none" /> The prostate, bilateral seminal vesicles and vas deferens are unremarkable grossly.<br clear="none" />4. Lymph nodes in _ bottles.<p><br clear="none" /></p><div>Tissue sampled are labelled as below.</div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div>ureter cut end <br clear="none" />MICROSCOPIC FINDINGS:<br clear="none" />A. Tumor histological type: urothelial carcinoma (or other types specified in the <br clear="none" />latest version of the WHO classification) <br clear="none" />B. Tumor histological grade: Grade __/2-tier system; Grade __ / 3-tier system<br clear="none" />C. Tumor invasion depth: <br clear="none" />__ Non-invasive papillary (pTa)<br clear="none" />__ Invades subepithelial connective tissue (pT1) <br clear="none" />__ Invades muscular propria (pT2) <br clear="none" />__ Other (specify) <br clear="none" />D. Urothelial carcinoma in situ: present / absent <br clear="none" />E. Lymphovascular invasion: present / absent <br clear="none" />F. Surgical margins: ??Tumor base: <br clear="none" />__ Free of tumor <br clear="none" />__ Presence of tumor element, with / without finding of muscular invasion<br clear="none" />G. Muscular element: present / absent<br clear="none" />H. Lymph node status</div></div></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
