    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS: (including pT and operation method)</div><div>1. Urothelial carcinoma (pT_) with presence/ absence of carcinoma in situ; urinary bladder; TUR-BT</div><div>2. Free / Presence of tumor; tumor base; resection</div><div><br/></div><div>PREVIOUS PATHOLOGICAL EXAM.:</div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS FINDINGS:</div><div>TUR-BUBT:</div><div>The specimen is composed of multiple tissue chips, measuring __ x __ x __ cm and ____ gm in toto. Included also is a small tissue (tumor base), about __ x __ x __ cm.</div><div><br/></div><div>CYSTECTOMY:</div><div><br/></div><div>Tissue sampled are labelled as below.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC FINDINGS:</div><div>A. Tumor histological type: urothelial carcinoma (or other types specified in the latest version of the WHO classification)</div><div>B. Tumor histological grade: low-grade   high-grade</div><div>C. Tumor invasion depth:</div><div>__ Non-invasive papillary (pTa)</div><div>__ Invades subepithelial connective tissue (pT1)</div><div>__ Invades muscular propria (pT2)</div><div>__ Tumor invades perivesicle tissue (pT3)</div><div>__ Tumor invades any of the following：prostate,uterus,vagina,pelvic wall,abdominall wall (pT4)</div><div>__ Other (specify)</div><div>"UC with muscle invasion, indeterminate for type of muscle invasion"</div><div>D. Urothelial carcinoma in situ: present / absent </div><div>E. Lymphovascular invasion: present / absent</div><div>F. Tumor base:</div><div>__ Free of tumor</div><div>__ Presence of tumor element, with / without finding of muscular invasion</div><div>G. <span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">Muscularis propria presence</span>:  __ Present;   __ Absent</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
