<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>GROSS:</div><div>Procedure: Abbomindal total hysterectomy</div><div>Specimen Integrity:  ___ Intact ___ Opened ___ Morcellated</div><div>Uterus: _ cm and _ gm.</div><div>Tumor: </div><div><span>    </span>Tumor Site ___ Uterine corpus __ Uterine cervix</div><div><span>    </span>Tumor Size: </div><div><span>    </span>Necrosis: Present/ Absent</div><div>Endometrium: _ cm</div><div>Myometrium: _ cm</div><div>Additional findings: </div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC FINDINGS:</div><div>Histologic Type: Leiomyosarcoma, mixed spindle</div><div>  (conventional), epithelioid and myxoid subtypes.</div><div>Tumor size: _ cm at greatest dimension</div><div>Surgical margin: free of tumor, with closest margin of __ cm.</div><div>Other Tissue/Organ Involvemen: Not identified.</div><div>Lymphovascular Invasion: Not identified.</div><div>pT Category:</div><div>pT1a: Tumor 5 cm or less in greatest dimension </div><div>pT1b: Tumor more than 5 cm</div><div>pT2a: Tumor involves adnexa</div><div>pT2b: Tumor involves other pelvic tissues</div><div>pT3a: Tumor infiltrates abdominal tissues in one site </div><div>pT3b: Tumor infiltrates abdominal tissues in more than one site</div><div>pT4: Tumor invades bladder or rectum</div><div>TNM Descriptors: Not applicable</div><div>Immunohistochemial studies:</div><div>  Desmin: diffusely positive</div><div>  SMA: diffusely positive</div><div>  S100: negative</div><div>  ALK: negative</div><div>  Cyclin D1: focally positive</div><div>  Myogenin: negative</div><div>Other findings:</div><div>  Cervix: chronic inflammation with squamous</div><div>  metaplasia.</div><div>  Endometrium: Proliferative phase.</div><div>  Myometrium: Small leiomyoma.</div><div>pTNM:  pT___N___ (AJCC cancer staging system, 8th edition)</div><div>TNM descriptors: not applicable; ___y(posttreatment); ___r(retreatment); ___a(autopsy); ___m(multiple);  </div><div>(sn) Sentinel nodes evaluated</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>(This case has been peer reviewed by two doctors.)</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
