    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Squamous cell carcinoma / Adenocarcinoma / Others (T_; FIGO _), with nodal status (N_,__/__); uterine cervix; radical hysterectomy, BSO, and bilateral pelvic LN dissection</div><div><br/></div><div>PREVIOUS PATHOLOGICAL EXAM:</div><div>1.20__-__-____:  ______; uterine cervix; biopsy / conization</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS FINDING:</div><div>[Uterus]  __ x __ x__ cm and ___ gm</div><div>1. Cervix: Tumor size ( __ x __ x __ cm), confined to the uterus (otherwise, specify the abnormal findings that affect tumor staging)</div><div>2. Vagina: __ cm long and (free of / invaded by) the tumor</div><div>3. Parametrium: ___ cm wide and  (free of / invaded by) the tumor</div><div>4. Endometrium: ___ cm  thick and unremarkable (otherwise, specify abnormal findings)</div><div>5. Myometrium: ___ cm thick and unremarkable (otherwise, specify abnormal findings)</div><div>[Bilateral ovaries and Fallopian tubes] unremarkable on appearance and sizes (otherwise, specify abnormal findings)</div><div>[Lymph nodes] described in detail below</div><div><br/></div><div>Tissues sampled are labeled as followings:</div><div>A      : vaginal cut margin</div><div>B,C  : cervix &amp; vagina, 12 o'clock         </div><div>D,E  : cervix &amp; vagina, 06 o'clock</div><div>F-H  : cervix &amp; vagina, 03 o'clock &amp; vagina (left side) and parametrium</div><div>I-K   : cervix &amp; vagina, 09 o'clock &amp; vagina (right side) and parametrium</div><div>L      : endometrium &amp; myometrium           </div><div>M     : right ovary &amp; fallopian tube       </div><div>N     : left ovary &amp; fallopian tube</div><div>O     : LN, Rt. common iliac (n= __/__)       </div><div> P     : LN, Rt. ext. iliac  (n= __/__) </div><div>Q     : LN, Rt. int. iliac (n= __/__)         </div><div>R,S  : LN, Rt. obturator  (n= __/__) </div><div>T     : LN, Rt. inguinal  (n= __/__) </div><div>U     : LN, Lt. common iliac  (n= __/__)       </div><div>V     : LN, Lt. ext. iliac  (n= __/__) </div><div>W    : LN, Lt. int. iliac  (n= __/__)         </div><div>X,Y : LN, Lt. obturator  (n= __/__) </div><div>Z     : LN, Lt. inguinal (n= __/__) </div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC FINDINGS:</div><div>1. Tumor histological type: squamous cell carcinoma (or others used in WHO classification) </div><div>2. Tumor histological grade: well / moderate / poor differentiation</div><div>3. Tumor size: __ (largest dimension) x __ x __ cm</div><div>4. Invasion depth/cervical wall thickness: __ mm/___mm (equal or less than / greater than 1/2 cervical wall; full thickness)</div><div>5. Tumor extension:</div><div>    a. Uterus: confined within the cervix; extended to the uterine corpus (specify the findings)</div><div>    b. Vaginal wall: absent / present (specify the findings and cut margins)</div><div>    c. Parametrium: absent / invaded  (specify the findings and cut margins)</div><div>6. Lymphovascular invasion:  absent / present</div><div>7. Lymph node status: Metastasis present in (none / ___) of the ___ LNs found (detailed above)</div><div>8. Other findings:</div><div>    a. Endometrium:</div><div>    b. Myometrium:</div><div>    c. Ovaries:</div><div>    d. Fallopian tubes: </div><div>    e.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Uterus_endometrial CA</title>
    <created>20150723T235739Z</created>
    <updated>20180403T065607Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source-url>file:///F:\2018%20AJCC%20學會版本\15-Endometrial%20cancer%20checklist.doc</source-url>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:<br clear="none" />
___ (pT_) with_out lymph node metastasis (), uterine corpus,<br clear="none" />
Laparoscopic staging operation (lparoscopically assisted vaginal hysterectomy, bilateral salpingo-oophorectomy, bilateral pelvic lymph node dissection, paraaortic LN sampling and cytology)<br clear="none" /><br clear="none" />
REFERENCE:</div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;-en-paragraph:true;"><br clear="none" /></div><div><br clear="none" />
GROSS FIDINGS:</div><div>Procedure</div><div>Tumor Site<br clear="none" />
#1. Uterus: __ x __ x __ cm and ___ gm<br clear="none" />
a. Tumor size: __ (largest dimension) x __ x ___ cm<br clear="none" />
b. Tumor location: fundus/body/lower uterine segment; no apparent tumor mass can be found;<br clear="none" />
the endometrium is diffusely thickened or diffusely involved by tumor.<br clear="none" />
c. Myometrium: free / presence of apparent tumor invasion<br clear="none" />
d. Cervix: free / presence of apparent tumor invasion<br clear="none" />
e. Others (affecting the level of staging):<br clear="none" />
#2. Ovary: right (__ x __ x __ cm); left ( __ x __ x __ cm)<br clear="none" />
Tube (length/diameter): right (__/__ cm); left (___/__ cm)<br clear="none" />
Free / Presence of tumor invasion at __________ (describe in detail)<br clear="none" />
#3. Groups of lymph nodes: in __ separate containers, described in detail below<br clear="none" />
a. Right pelvic LNs: _ tissue fragments_ (_ x _ x _ cm_in total)<br clear="none" />
b. Left pelvic LNs: _ tissue fragments_ (_ x _ x _ cm_in total)<br clear="none" />
c. Para-aortic LNs: _ tissue fragments_ (_ x _ x _ cm_in total)<br clear="none" />
d. _ LNs: _ tissue fragments_ (_ x _ x _ cm)<br clear="none" />
e. _ LNs: _ tissue fragments_ (_ x _ x _ cm)</div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;-en-paragraph:true;"><br clear="none" /></div><div>Tissues sampled are labeled as followings,<br clear="none" />
R_: tumor (mapping: _)<br clear="none" />
R_: lower uterine segment<br clear="none" />
R_: non-tumor endometrium and myometrium<br clear="none" />
R_: myomatous nodule<br clear="none" />
R_: cervix<br clear="none" />
R_: right adnexa<br clear="none" />
R_: left adnexa<br clear="none" />
right common iliac LN ( __/ __)<br clear="none" />
right internal iliac LN ( __/ __)<br clear="none" />
right external iliac LN ( __/ __)<br clear="none" />
right obturator LN ( __/ __)<br clear="none" />
left common iliac LN ( __/ __)<br clear="none" />
left internal iliac LN ( __/ __)<br clear="none" />
left external iliac LN ( __/ __)<br clear="none" />
left obturator LN ( __/ __)<br clear="none" />
para-aortic LN ( __/ __)</div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;-en-paragraph:true;"><br clear="none" /></div><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;-en-paragraph:true;"><br clear="none" /></div><div>MICROSCOPIC FINDINGS:<br clear="none" />
1.Tumor histological type: ____<br clear="none" />
Reference: Endometroid adenocarcinoma (with squamous differentiation; villoglandular<br clear="none" />
variant secretory variant; ciliated cell variant); Mucinous adenocarcinoma; Serous<br clear="none" />
adenocarcinoma; Clear cell adenocarcinoma; Mixed cell adenocarcinoma; Squamous cell<br clear="none" />
carcinoma; Transitional cell carcinoma; Small cell carcinoma; Undifferentiated carcinoma;<br clear="none" />
Others<br clear="none" />
2.Histological grade: Grade ___<br clear="none" />
Reference: Non-squamous solid growth pattern: G1 (5% or less); G2 (6—50%); G3 (>50%)</div><div>Serous, clear cell, carcinosarcoma and mixed mesodermal tumors are Grade 3</div><div>   NOTE: Notable nuclear atypica,</div><div>   which exceeds that which is routinely expected for the architectural grade,</div><div>   increases the tumor grade by 1.</div><div>3.Myometrial invasion:<br clear="none" />
a. Less (T1a) / Greater ( T1b) than one-half of myometrium<br clear="none" />
b. Invasion depth/ myometrial wall thickness: __ cm /__ cm</div><div>Uterine Serosa Involvement<br clear="none" />
4.Cervical Stromal Involvement</div><div>Free; presence of glandular invasion (T1) / stromal invasion (T2)</div><div>Other Tissue/ Organ Involvement<br clear="none" />
5.Blood/lymphatic vessel invasion: present / absent<br clear="none" />
6.7. Margins (required only if cervix and/or parametrium/paracervix is involved by carcinoma)</div><div>(i) Ectocervical/Vaginal Cuff Margin:  Free        Not Free</div><div>        (ii) Parametrial/Paracervical Margin:   Free         Not Free</div><div><br clear="none" />
7.Lymph node status: metastasis present in none / ____ of the ____ lymph nodes found (with</div><div>details provided above in the sampling description) </div><div>isolated tumor cells/ micrometastasis/ macrometastasis</div><div>8.Additional findings:<br clear="none" />
a. Cervix:<br clear="none" />
b. Endometrium (non-tumorous part):<br clear="none" />
c. Myometrium:<br clear="none" />
d. Ovary and tube:<br clear="none" />
9.Immunostains: ER (positive/negative), PR (positive/negative).</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Uterus_prolapse</title>
    <created>20150723T091135Z</created>
    <updated>20230102T045502Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Uterus, laparoscopic-assisted vaginal hysterectomy ---</div><div>1. Epidermidalization/Parakeratosis, consistent with prolapse, cervix uteri and vaginal wall</div><div>2. , myometrium</div><div>3. , endometrium</div><div>4., left ovary</div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div>The specimen is a uterus measuring _ x _ x _ cm and _ gm. The serosal surface is smooth and glistening. The exocervix is diffusely roughened and eroded. On opening, the endometrium and myometrium measure _ cm and</div><div>_ cm in thickness respectively. One myomatous nodule is identified, measuring _ x _ x _ cm. On cut sections, whorls of whitish fibrous tissue with degeneration are noted. _ fragments of vaginal wall are seen, measuring up to _ x _ x _ cm.</div><div><br/></div><div>Representative sections are submitted in 3 cassettes.</div><div>A1: cervix</div><div>A2: endometrium and myometrium</div><div>A3: vaginal wall</div><div><br/></div><div style="margin-top: 1em;margin-bottom: 1em;-en-paragraph:true;"><br clear="none" /></div><div>MICROSCOPIC FINDINGS:</div><div style="margin-top: 1em;margin-bottom: 1em;-en-paragraph:true;"><div>The cervical tissue and vaginal tissue show parakeratotic surface. Inactive</div><div>endometrium is noted. There is no evidence of malignancy.</div></div><div>The uterine cerivix shows parakeratosis, subepithelial lymphocytic infiltration and focal ulceration. The endometrium reveals unreamrkable glands. The myometrium shows nodular lesion composed of bland-looking smooth muscle bundles. The vaginal wall tissue shows parakeratosis.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
