<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div style="display:none;--en-chs:&quot;&quot;"> </div><div>PATHOLOGIC DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>_ testis, radical orchiectomy --- ___ (pT_).</div><div><br/></div><div>Gross description:</div><div>The specimen measures _ g and consists of a testis</div><div>(_ x _ x _ cm) with epididymis (_ x _ x _  cm) and a</div><div>segment spermatic cord (_ cm in length and _ cm in</div><div>diameter). The testis is occupied by a tumor measuring</div><div>_ x _ x _ cm. On cut section, the tumor shows pale yellow</div><div>cut surface with focal necrosis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows: </div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Histologic Type: ____</div><div>Tumor Size:</div><div>  Greatest dimension of main tumor mass: ___ cm</div><div>Tumor Extent: Limited to testis with rete testis invasion</div><div>Lymphovascular Invasion: Absent  Present</div><div>pT_:</div><div>Margin Status: Free, _ cm in distance.</div><div>Regional Lymph Node Status: Not applicable (no regional</div><div>  lymph nodes submitted or found)</div><div>pTNM: pT_N_ (AJCC cancer staging system, 8th edition)</div><div>TNM descriptors: not applicable</div><div>Immunohistochemical stains:</div><div>  CD30: Negative; CD117: Positive.</div><div>Additional Findings:</div><div>  Epididymis: Free of tumor</div><div>  Spermatic cord: Free of tumor</div><div>  Residual seminiferous tubules show atrophy with</div><div>    focal microlith and presence of germ cell neoplasia in</div><div>    situ (GCNIS).</div><div><br/></div><div>(This case has been peer reviewed by two doctors.)</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
